on%20with%20a%202.5%25%20interest%20rate%20in%202023%20when%20rates%20were%20around%206%25%20.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20lower%20mortgage%20rate%2C%20attained%20via%20an%20assumable%20mortgage%2C%20will%20allow%20them%20to%20save%20%2440%2C000%20over%2028%20years.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20couple%20have%20used%20their%20savings%20to%20pay%20down%20their%20medical%20debt%20and%20purchase%20a%20new%20car.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20as-told-to%20essay%20is%20based%20on%20a%20conversation%20with%20Amy%20Yzaguirre%2C%2040%2C%20a%20student%20and%20barista%2C%20who%20with%20her%20husband%20purchased%20a%20home%20with%20an%20assumable%20mortgage%20in%20Tigard%2C%20Oregon%2C%20in%20March%202023.%20An%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-to-get-lower-cost-effective-mortgage-rates-2023-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3Eassumable%20mortgage%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%20allows%20qualifying%20buyers%20to%20acquire%20the%20interest%20rate%2C%20current%20principal%20balance%2C%20and%20other%20conditions%20of%20a%20seller's%20existing%20loan.%20Not%20all%20loans%20can%20be%20assumed.%20The%20essay%20has%20been%20edited%20for%20length%20and%20clarity.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20grew%20up%20in%20the%20Portland%20area%2C%20but%20moved%20to%20Boise%20in%202017.%20In%202022%2C%20my%20husband%20and%20I%20decided%20to%20move%20back%20to%20Oregon.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20husband%20had%20applied%20for%20some%20jobs%20in%20Portland%20and%20got%20a%20position%2C%20but%20we%20had%20just%20refinanced%20our%20Boise%20home.%20Since%20we%20had%20signed%20a%20no-flip%20clause%2C%20we%20couldn't%20sell%20it%20until%20April%202022.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20planned%20that%20he%20would%20move%20to%20Portland%20and%20live%20with%20a%20friend%20while%20our%20son%20and%20I%20stayed%20back%20and%20got%20the%20house%20ready%20to%20be%20sold%20in%20April.%20Then%2C%20we%20would%20join%20him%20and%20buy%20a%20house.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20in%20January%202022%2C%20I%20was%20diagnosed%20with%20stage%20four%20non-Hodgkin's%20lymphoma.%20I%20didn't%20want%20to%20undergo%20half%20of%20my%20chemo%20treatment%20in%20Boise%20and%20the%20other%20half%20in%20Portland%2C%20so%20we%20had%20to%20figure%20out%20a%20way%20to%20be%20together%20as%20a%20family%20while%20I%20underwent%20chemotherapy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22720%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Amy%20Yzaguirre%20and%20her%20husband%20pose%20in%20front%20of%20the%20RV%20they%20purchased.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65f9d7d1895d822030324f37%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22542%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EYzaguirre%20and%20her%20husband%20in%20front%20of%20their%20RV.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Amy%20Yzaguirre%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20had%20to%20keep%20the%20house%20until%20April%2C%20but%20we%20couldn't%20afford%20to%20pay%20two%20mortgages%20or%20pay%20rent%20and%20a%20mortgage.%20A%20family%20friend%20gave%20us%20the%20idea%20to%20buy%20an%20RV%20and%20live%20on%20my%20parents'%20land%20in%20Oregon.%20We%20lived%20there%20for%20eight%20months.%20It%20was%20pretty%20rough%2C%20but%20we%20made%20it%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20March%20of%202022%2C%20we%20started%20looking%20at%20houses%20through%20our%20realtor.%20I%20was%20in%20the%20middle%20of%20chemo%2C%20but%20on%20the%20days%20that%20I%20would%20feel%20good%2C%20we%20would%20meet%20up%20with%20brokers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20suggested%2C%20%26quot%3BTo%20get%20the%20type%20of%20mortgage%20loan%20that%20you%20want%2C%20you%20need%20to%20wait%20until%20you're%20back%20to%20work.%26quot%3B%20So%2C%20we%20decided%20to%20pause%20our%20home%20search%20until%20then.%20While%20waiting%2C%20we%20got%20our%20credit%20in%20a%20good%20spot.%20When%20August%20came%20around%20and%20I%20got%20a%20job%2C%20we%20started%20seriously%20looking%20at%20houses.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EFinding%20an%20affordable%20home%20to%20buy%20was%20difficult%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20wanted%20to%20live%20in%20the%20suburb%20that%20my%20parents%20lived%20in%2C%20called%20Tigard%2C%20but%20the%20area%20was%20too%20expensive%20for%20us%20and%20the%20real%20estate%20market%20was%20fairly%20competitive.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20funny%20how%20an%20area%20can%20be%20a%20nice%2C%20family-friendly%2C%20affordable%20place%20to%20live%2C%20and%20then%20all%20of%20a%20sudden%20it%20becomes%20overpopulated%20and%20it's%20not%20nearly%20as%20reasonable%20as%20it%20used%20to%20be.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20eventually%20decided%20to%20look%20in%20the%20Sherwood%20area%20instead.%20At%20this%20point%2C%20I%20had%20beaten%20cancer%20and%20was%20in%20remission.%20My%20husband%20and%20I%20were%20excited%20that%20we%20could%20take%20the%20next%20step%20and%20buy%20a%20new%20house.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20qualified%20for%20a%20substantial%20loan%20through%20our%20mortgage%20company%2C%20but%20we%20didn't%20want%20our%20monthly%20payments%20to%20be%20too%20high.%20We%20set%20our%20budget%20for%20a%20home%20at%20no%20more%20than%20%24450%2C000%20%E2%80%94%20but%20even%20that%20was%20a%20bit%20of%20a%20stretch.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223024%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20Yzaguirre's%20Oregon%20home.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65f9d8862417f97b87cd6a1a%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%224032%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAmy%20Yzaguirre's%20Oregon%20home.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Amy%20Yzaguirre%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20we%20looked%2C%20we%20really%20couldn't%20find%20many%20homes%20that%20checked%20all%20the%20boxes%20for%20that%20amount.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20in%20September%202022%2C%20we%20found%20a%20townhouse%20that%20was%20on%20the%20market%20for%20%24416%2C000.%20On%20a%20flier%20for%20the%20home%2C%20its%20seller%20had%20written%20that%20if%20we%20wanted%20to%20assume%20her%20loan%2C%20she%20was%20locked%20in%20at%202.5%25.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20didn't%20necessarily%20draw%20us%20in%20because%20we%20didn't%20quite%20know%20what%20that%20meant.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20was%20more%20interested%20in%20the%20fact%20that%20it%20was%20a%201%2C500-square-foot%20townhouse%20that%20had%20everything%20we%20wanted%2C%20like%20a%20backyard%2C%20a%20big%20garage%2C%20and%20an%20open%20floor%20plan%20with%20hardwood%20floors.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20time%2C%20I%20believe%20mortgage%20rates%20were%20close%20to%206%25.%20If%20we%20had%20a%20traditional%20mortgage%2C%20our%20monthly%20payment%20would%20have%20been%20about%20%243%2C000%20a%20month.%20I%20remember%20being%20like%20%26quot%3BOkay%2C%20that's%20pretty%20high%2C%20but%20I%20think%20we%20can%20make%20it%20work.%20We're%20just%20going%20to%20have%20to%20be%20really%20careful.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EAn%20assumable%20mortgage%20was%20too%20irresistible%20to%20pass%20up%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20told%20our%20realtor%20about%20the%20home%20and%20asked%20her%20what%20an%20assumable%20mortgage%20was.%20She%20said%20%26quot%3BYou'll%20have%20to%20talk%20to%20our%20mortgage%20broker.%20I%20don't%20really%20have%20any%20experience%20with%20that%20and%20don't%20know%20what%20it%20entails.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20asked%20the%20mortgage%20broker%2C%20and%20he%20admitted%2C%20%26quot%3BWell%2C%20we%20haven't%20dealt%20with%20this%20in%20probably%20about%2030%20years%2C%20so%20I'm%20not%20entirely%20familiar%20with%20the%20process.%20But%20essentially%2C%20when%20you%20assume%20a%20loan%2C%20you're%20taking%20over%20the%20seller's%20mortgage.%20If%20you%20qualify%2C%20you%20can%20adopt%20their%20locked-in%20rate%2C%20and%20you%20don't%20have%20to%20pay%20current%20mortgage%20rates.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20warned%20us%20that%20the%20seller's%20mortgage%20company%20was%20not%20going%20to%20hold%20our%20hand%20through%20the%20process.%20But%20if%20we%20were%20willing%20to%20put%20in%20a%20rigorous%20amount%20of%20work%20and%20do%20a%20lot%20of%20bugging%2C%20we%20should%20definitely%20try%20it%20because%20it%20would%20save%20us%20a%20lot%20of%20money.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20did%20the%20math.%20The%20seller%20was%20locked%20in%20at%202.5%25%2C%20so%20if%20we%20qualified%20to%20assume%20the%20loan%2C%20our%20mortgage%20would%20be%20a%20little%20over%20%242%2C100%20a%20month%20versus%20the%20over%20%243%2C000%20we%20would%20be%20paying%20with%20a%20traditional%20mortgage%20at%20current%20market%20rates.%20It%20would%20save%20us%20over%20%2440%2C000%20in%20the%20long%20run.%20That%20would%20give%20us%20wiggle%20room%20and%20allow%20us%20to%20continue%20our%20lifestyle%20instead%20of%20having%20to%20scale%20back.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20sounded%20amazing%2C%20so%20my%20husband%20and%20I%20decided%20to%20pursue%20the%20loan%20assumption.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EIt's%20not%20easy%20assuming%20a%20loan%20%E2%80%94%20and%20it%20took%20forever%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20March%202023%2C%20we%20purchased%20our%20home%20for%20%24418%2C900%20and%20made%20a%20downpayment%20of%20%2448%2C000.%20The%20home%20had%20a%2030-year%20fixed-rate%20mortgage%2C%20with%2028%20years%20left%20on%20a%20%24383%2C000%20Federal%20Housing%20Administration%20(FHA)%20loan.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20worked%20with%20Flagstar%20to%20assume%20the%20mortgage%20and%20they%20assigned%20us%20an%20advocate.%20He%20was%20really%20nice%20and%20helped%20us%20through%20the%20process.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20end%2C%20we%20ended%20up%20submitting%20over%20200%20documents%2C%20and%20the%20process%20took%20three%20full%20months.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20a%20certain%20point%2C%20my%20husband%20was%20over%20it%20and%20just%20wanted%20to%20go%20with%20a%20normal%20mortgage.%20I%20had%20to%20assure%20him%20I%20could%20take%20care%20of%20it%20and%20that%20it%20would%20all%20be%20worth%20it%20%E2%80%94%20we%20just%20had%20to%20be%20patient.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22578%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Yzaguirre's%20husband%20and%20son.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65f9db7b2417f97b87cd6b2f%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22434%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EYzaguirre's%20husband%20and%20son.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Amy%20Yzaguirre%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20mortgage%20broker%20we%20originally%20spoke%20to%20was%20right%20%E2%80%94%20as%20the%20company%20processing%20the%20assumable%20mortgage%20isn't%20making%20any%20money%2C%20you%20really%20have%20to%20advocate%20for%20yourself%2C%20jump%20in%20there%2C%20and%20ask%20questions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20tell%20anybody%20who%20has%20asked%20me%20about%20assuming%20loans%20that%20it's%20going%20to%20take%20a%20long%20time%2C%20and%20it%20will%20be%20grueling.%20The%20process%20will%20humble%20you%20in%20some%20ways%20too%20because%20you%20start%20doubting%20yourself%2C%20like%2C%20%26quot%3BAm%20I%20a%20horrible%20financial%20person%3F%20Why%20did%20they%20need%20so%20much%20information%3F%20Am%20I%20not%20doing%20this%20right%3F%20Is%20there%20something%20that%20I've%20done%20wrong%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20once%20you%20get%20through%20the%20process%2C%20you%20should%20be%20able%20to%20get%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20just%20takes%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EThe%20hard%20work%20getting%20the%20assumable%20mortgage%20was%20worth%20it%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20living%20in%20a%20tiny%2021-foot%20RV%2C%20buying%20a%20home%20gave%20us%20freedom%20and%20a%20new%20beginning.%20It%20also%20helped%20me%20not%20feel%20boxed%20in%20anymore.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222316%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Yzaguirre%20and%20her%20husband.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65f9daf34af076d3cf91ba3d%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221737%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAmy%20Yzaguirre%20and%20her%20husband.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Amy%20Yzaguirre%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EEven%20though%20I%20was%20fortunate%20to%20have%20good%20insurance%20during%20chemotherapy%20%E2%80%94%20once%20I%20hit%20a%20certain%20deductible%2C%20insurance%2