asonable%2C%20or%20at%20least%20more%20reasonable%2C%20with%20some%20genuine%20intention%20to%20provide%20good%20leadership%20to%20their%20country.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EI%20am%20not%20suggesting%20that%20the%20initial%20good%20intention%20is%20always%20the%20case.%20The%20main%20result%20in%20this%20paper%20is%20to%20show%20that%20no%20matter%20where%20an%20authoritarian%20leader%20starts%20from%20there%20will%20be%20a%20tendency%20to%20deteriorate%20over%20time.%20However%2C%20I%20believe%20that%20to%20deny%20that%20there%20may%20be%20good%20intentions%20at%20the%20start%2C%20as%20though%20evil%20intention%20is%20an%20axiomatic%20truth%2C%20hurts%20an%20objective%20analysis%20of%20dictators%20and%20totalitarian%20regimes%20and%20thereby%20thwarts%20the%20development%20of%20policies%20and%20strategy%20to%20block%20such%20unwanted%20turns%20of%20events%20as%20we%20have%20seen%20repeatedly%20through%20history.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EExamples%20jump%20out%20at%20us%3A%20Joseph%20Stalin%2C%20Benito%20Mussolini%2C%20Hugo%20Chavez%2C%20Fidel%20Castro%2C%20Kim%20II-sung%2C%20Robert%20Mugabe%2C%20Zine%20El%20Abidine%20Ben%20Ali%2C%20Muammar%20Gaddafi%2C%20Daniel%20Ortega.%20In%20case%20these%20examples%20seem%20inadequate%2C%20after%20I%20began%20working%20on%20this%20paper%2C%20Putin%20invaded%20Ukraine%2C%20giving%20us%20a%20reminder%20that%20he%20had%20been%20left%20out.%20So%20let%20me%20add%3A%20and%20Vladimir%20Putin.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20paper%20uses%20simple%2C%20plausible%20assumptions%20and%20provides%2C%20by%20a%20step-by-step%20analysis%2C%20a%20surprisingly%20clear%20explanation%20of%20this%20propensity%20of%20leaders%20in%20power%20for%20long%20to%20morph%20into%20someone%20tyrannical%20and%20evil.%20What%20the%20paper%20tries%20to%20explain%20is%20the%20puzzle%20summed%20up%20by%20Stephen%20%3Cspan%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20data-open%3D%5C%22ref23%5C%22%20data-google-interstitial%3D%5C%22false%5C%22%3EKinzer%20(2021)%3C%2Fa%3E%3A%20%E2%80%98For%20most%20of%20his%20life%20%5BDaniel%20Ortega%5D%20was%20in%20passionate%20rebellion%20against%20%5BSomoza%E2%80%99s%20dictatorship%20and%5D%20everything%20it%20represented.%20Then%2C%20in%20what%20seemed%20an%20astonishing%20about-face%2C%20he%20began%20replicating%20it.%20With%20precision%20and%20design%2C%20he%20has%20created%20an%20insular%2C%20dynastic%20tyranny%20that%20eerily%20resembles%20the%20one%20against%20which%20he%20fought%20decades%20ago.%E2%80%99%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20strong%20political%20leaders%20who%20stay%20in%20power%20for%20a%20long%20time%2C%20there%20are%20many%20changes%20that%20occur%20in%20their%20environment%20that%20can%20be%20cause%20for%20concern.%20We%20know%20that%20the%20information%20and%20news%20that%20such%20leaders%20get%20become%20increasingly%20biased.%20Their%20staff%20and%20minions%2C%20concerned%20not%20to%20upset%20the%20leader%2C%20give%20their%20boss%20the%20information%20the%20boss%20would%20like%20to%20hear.%20It%20is%20likely%20that%20Mao%20Zedong%20did%20not%20learn%20for%20a%20long%20time%20that%20his%20Great%20Leap%20Forward%20had%20failed%20and%20was%20causing%20one%20of%20the%20great%20famines%20in%20world%20history%2C%20instead.%20It%20is%20likely%20that%20what%20Putin%20believes%20is%20happening%20in%20Ukraine%20is%20far%20from%20what%20is%20happening%20in%20Ukraine.%20His%20reputation%20for%20tyranny%20and%20brutality%20must%20ensure%20that%20his%20staff%20will%20give%20him%20the%20news%20he%20wants%20to%20hear.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFurther%2C%20the%20psychology%20of%20tyrants%20is%20often%20very%20different%20from%20ordinary%20mortals.%20Some%20of%20them%20are%20probably%20unaware%20of%20their%20own%20brutality%20or%20under%20the%20belief%20that%20it%20is%20done%20in%20the%20best%20interest%20of%20the%20nation.%20It%20is%20impossible%20to%20know%20if%20they%20actually%20believe%20in%20this%20or%20create%20these%20delusions%20to%20be%20able%20to%20live%20with%20themselves.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20aim%20of%20this%20paper%20is%20to%20focus%20on%20a%20slender%20cut%20of%20this%20reality%20and%20draw%20attention%20to%20a%20natural%20result.%20No%20matter%20what%20the%20initial%20intention%20of%20a%20leader%20seeking%20power%2C%20it%20is%20easy%20to%20take%20steps%20to%20prolong%20their%20tenure%2C%20which%20one%20step%20at%20a%20time%20may%20seem%20natural%2C%20but%20in%20their%20totality%20traps%20the%20leader%20in%20political%20evil%20and%20oppression%20that%20they%20cannot%20escape.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20most%20poignant%20statement%20of%20this%20tragic%20human%20predicament%20occurs%20in%20Shakespeare%E2%80%99s%20Macbeth%20(Act%20III%2C%20Scene%20IV)%2C%20when%20Macbeth%20tells%20his%20wife%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CI%20am%20in%20blood%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EStepp%E2%80%99d%20in%20so%20far%20that%2C%20should%20I%20wade%20no%20more%2C%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EReturning%20were%20as%20tedious%20as%20go%20o%E2%80%99er.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIf%20the%20leaders%20are%20innately%20evil%2C%20their%20ending%20up%20practicing%20evil%2C%20would%20not%20be%20a%20surprising%20result.%20By%20focusing%20on%20the%20case%20of%20leaders%20with%20good%20intention%20and%20then%20showing%20how%20they%20end%20up%20as%20tyrants%2C%20this%20paper%20explains%20why%20this%20transformation%20of%20leaders%20who%20remain%20long%20in%20power%20is%20so%20ubiquitous.%20It%20should%20be%20emphasized%20that%20the%20model%20is%20not%20about%20where%20the%20leaders%20start%E2%80%94good%20or%20bad%2C%20but%20about%20the%20process%20by%20which%20they%20%3Cem%3Edeteriorate%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20wherever%20they%20start.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDictator%E2%80%99s%20choice%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThough%20the%20paper%20is%20an%20exercise%20in%20theory%2C%20it%20owes%20its%20origin%20to%20a%20personal%20experience.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20September%202013%2C%20I%20met%20Daniel%20Ortega%20in%20Managua.%20The%20meeting%20had%20nothing%20to%20do%20with%20the%20World%20Bank%20mission%20that%20had%20taken%20me%20to%20Nicaragua.%20As%20a%20student%20in%20India%20and%2C%20later%2C%20England%2C%20I%20had%20heard%20and%20admired%20the%20achievement%20of%20Ortega%20in%20overthrowing%20Somoza%E2%80%99s%20corrupt%20regime.%20It%20was%20a%20long%20meeting%20where%20we%20talked%20about%20the%20Sandinista%20revolution%20and%20the%20challenges%20faced%20by%20Nicaragua.%20Given%20the%20sordid%20accounts%20that%20have%20subsequently%20emerged%20of%20Ortega%E2%80%99s%20oppressive%20and%20tyrannical%20behavior%20(%3Cspan%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20data-open%3D%5C%22ref23%5C%22%20data-google-interstitial%3D%5C%22false%5C%22%3EKinzer%2C%202021%3C%2Fa%3E)%2C%20I%20regret%20the%20decision%20to%20meet%20him.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EI%20was%20also%20left%20with%20a%20troubling%20question%3A%20How%20%3Cem%3Ecould%3C%2Fem%3E%20this%20happen%3F%20How%20could%20Daniel%20Ortega%2C%20who%20struggled%2C%20suffered%20and%20eventually%20overthrew%20the%20corrupt%20tyrant%2C%20Anastasio%20Somoza%20Debayle%2C%20morph%20into%20a%20creature%20similar%20to%20the%20one%20he%20overthrew%3F%20Was%20it%20a%20case%20of%20one%20freak%20individual%20and%20his%20psychology%2C%20or%20is%20there%20something%20generic%20about%20authoritarianism%20that%20makes%20it%20deteriorate%20over%20time.%20The%20model%20that%20follows%20is%20an%20exercise%20in%20atonement%20through%20model%20building.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20paper%20presents%20a%20theoretical%20structure%20inspired%20by%20the%20above%20reality.%20What%20the%20paper%20shows%20is%20that%20a%20modicum%20of%20dynamic%20inconsistency%20or%20present%20bias%2C%20which%20is%20a%20widely%20noted%20trait%20in%20human%20beings%20(%3Cspan%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20data-open%3D%5C%22ref30%5C%22%20data-google-interstitial%3D%5C%22false%5C%22%3EPhelps%20and%20Pollak%2C%201968%3C%2Fa%3E%3B%20%3Cspan%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20data-open%3D%5C%22ref28%5C%22%20data-google-interstitial%3D%5C%22false%5C%22%3EO%E2%80%99Donoghue%20and%20Rabin%2C%201999%3C%2Fa%3E%3B%20%3Cspan%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20data-open%3D%5C%22ref24%5C%22%20data-google-interstitial%3D%5C%22false%5C%22%3EKleinberg%20and%20Oren%2C%202014%3C%2Fa%3E%3B%20%3Cspan%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20data-open%3D%5C%22ref13%5C%22%20data-google-interstitial%3D%5C%22false%5C%22%3EChakraborty%2C%202021%3C%2Fa%3E)%2C%20gives%20us%20this%20result.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20one%20ponders%20about%20this%2C%20it%20becomes%20clear%20that%20this%20is%20not%20just%20a%20theoretical%20possibility%20but%2C%20being%20based%20on%20realistic%20assumptions%2C%20it%20gives%20us%20insight%20into%20this%20troubling%20phenomenon%2C%20of%20strong%20leaders%20morphing%20into%20tyrants.%20Often%20big%20problems%20have%20simple%20root%20causes.%20What%20this%20paper%20shows%20is%20that%20the%20reason%20dictators%20morph%20into%20tyrants%20is%2C%20in%20terms%20of%20logic%2C%20the%20same%20as%20why%20George%20Akerlof%20procrastinated%20mailing%20Joseph%20Stiglitz%E2%80%99s%20parcel%20from%20India%2C%20after%20Stiglitz%20returned%20home%20and%20Akerlof%20stayed%20on%20for%20a%20while%20more%20(%3Cspan%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20data-open%3D%5C%22ref1%5C%22%20data-google-interstitial%3D%5C%22false%5C%22%3EAkerlof%2C%201991%3C%2Fa%3E).%20Every%20morning%2C%20%5Bthe%20thought%20of%5D%20the%20transactions%20cost%20of%20going%20to%20the%20post-office%20and%20standing%20in%20the%20queue%20that%20day%20acquired%20a%20salience%20in%20his%20mind%2C%20which%20made%20him%20decide%20he%20would%20mail%20it%20the%20next%20day.%20It%20was%20this%20series%20of%20present-biased%20decisions%20that%20led%20to%20the%20long%20procrastination.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20gist%20of%20the%20argument%20in%20the%20context%20of%20political%20leaders%20is%20the%20following.%20Consider%20a%20person%20who%20comes%20to%20power%20by%20overthrowing%20a%20bad%20leader%2C%20as%20Daniel%20Ortega%20did%20by%20overthrowing%20Anastasio%20Somoza%20Debayle.%20The%20new%20leader%2C%20even%20while%20helping%20the%20country%20to%20do%20better%2C%20will%20soon%20face%20the%20decision%20of%20whether%20to%20seek%20more%20time%20in%20office.%20Politics%20is%20a%20tough%20game%2C%20where%20you%20often%20have%20to%20indulge%20in%20evil%20acts%20in%20order%20to%20escape%20the%20fate%20of%20being%20evicted%20from%20power.%20So%20the%20person%20has%20to%20decide%20how%20far%20to%20go%20in%20terms%20of%20political%20intrigue%20and%20ruthless%20acts%20in%20order%20to%20stay%20in%20power.%20A%20common%20feature%20in%20making%20this%20optimization%20decision%20is%20dynamic%20inconsistency.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIf%20the%20leader%20indulges%20in%20a%20certain%20amount%20of%20evil%20in%20order%20to%20remain%20in%20power%20and%20does%20thereby%20manage%20to%20stay%20in%20power%2C%20then%20during%20the%20next%20term%20or%20further%20in%20the%20future%20there%20may%20be%20an%20additional%20reason%20to%20want%20to%20stay%20in%20power.%20The%20evil%20acts%20of%20the%20earlier%20terms%20in%20office%20could%20mean%20that%20exit%20from%20office%20will%20be%20more%20costly.%20You%20will%20face%20inquiries%20about%20your%20acts%20while%20in%20office%20and%20may%20be%20punished%20%3Cem%3E%5Bsee%20footnote%201%3C%2Fem%3E%5D.%20This%20will%20prompt%20greater%20evil%20acts%20to%20stay%20on%20in%20office%2C%20and%20that%20will%20make%20the%20exit%20option%20even%20worse%2C%20and%20the%20inexorable%20logic%20of%20this%20continues.%20Gaddafi%20must%20have%20realized%2C%20midway%20through%2C%20that%20voluntary%20exit%20was%20no%20longer%20an%20option%20for%20him.%20If%20he%20had%20done%20the%20full%20dynamic%20optimization%20at%20the%20start%20he%20may%20never%20have%20gone%20down%20this%20route.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhat%20makes%20the%20ongoing%20Ukraine%20war%20so%20dangerous%20is%20that%20Putin%20is%20fast%20losing%20all%20exit%20options.%20We%20have%20enough%20evidence%20and%20analysis%20from%20behavioral%20economics%20to%20know%20that%20from%20procrastinators%20to%20drug%20addicts%20many%20fall%20into%20this%20trap.%20What%20the%20present%20paper%20argues%20is%20so%20may%20dictators%20and%20the%20final%20outcome%20can%20be%20bad%20for%20all.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EConversely%2C%20leaders%20who%20have%20got%20out%20of%20power%20have%20on%20occasions%20paid%20a%20heavy%20price%20for%20it.%20%3Cspan%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20data-open%3D%5C%22ref15%5C%22%20data-google-interstitial%3D%5C%22false%5C%22%3ECooter%20%26amp%3B%20Sch%C3%A4fer%20(2012)%3C%2Fa%3E%20refer%20to%20this%20as%20the%20%E2%80%98dictator%E2%80%99s%20dilemma.%E2%80%99%20A%20good%20illustration%20of%20this%20comes%20from%20Chile%E2%80%99s%20General%20Augusto%20Pinochet.%20He%20came%20to%20power%20after%20a%20brutal%20military%20coup%20in%201973%2C%20with%20non-negligible%20help%20from%20the%20CIA%2C%20against%20the%20democratically-elected%20leader%20Salvador%20Allende.%20He%20quickly%20morphed%20into%20a%20dictator%2C%20and%20ruled%20the%20country%20with%20an%20iron%20hand%20over%20more%20than%20a%20decade%2C%20killing%20thousands%20of%20opponent%20and%20torturing%20hundreds%20and%20thousands%20of%20his%20opponents%2C%20mainly%20leftists%20and%20socialists%2C%20during%20his%20term%20as%20leader%20of%20the%20nation.%20In%201990%20he%20got%20out%20of%20power%20by%20offering%20his%20resignation.%20However%2C%20it%20was%20not%20a%20good%20life%20after%20exiting%20from%20power.%20He%20was%20soon%20charged%20with%20human%20rights%20violation%2C%20murder%20and%20torture%20during%20his%20term%20as%20president%20and%20was%20arrested%20in%202004.%20Citing%20the%20case%20of%20Augusto%20Pinochet%2C%20%3Cspan%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20data-open%3D%5C%22ref15%5C%22%20data-google-interstitial%3D%5C%22false%5C%22%3ECooter%20and%20Sch%C3%A4fer%20(2012%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20p.%20219)%20point%20out%2C%20%E2%80%98This%20story%20depicts%20a%20dilemma%3A%20an%20aging%20dictator%20wants%20to%20resign%20from%20power%2C%20but%20he%20fears%20prosecution%20for%20crimes.%20His%20only%20effective%20guarantee%20against%20prosecution%20is%20to%20retain%20the%20power%20that%20he%20wants%20to%20relinquish.%E2%80%99%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDictator%20morphing%3A%20a%20model%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETo%20capture%20this%20dilemma%20simply%2C%20let%20us%20assume%20that%20the%20political%20calendar%20is%20broken%20up%20into%20terms%2C%20say%20four%20years%20for%20each%20term.%20Once%20in%20office%2C%20you%20are%20there%20for%20one%20term.%20During%20that%20term%2C%20you%20do%20many%20things%20as%20leader%20but%20you%20also%20have%20to%20decide%20whether%20to%20fight%20to%20stay%20on%20for%20another%20term.%20Consider%20the%20problem%20in%20the%20first%20term.%20It%20is%20a%20new%20leader%20and%20he%20has%20to%20decide%20his%20strategy.%20Suppose%20the%20amount%20of%20evil%20you%20indulge%20in%20is%20an%20element%20of%20%5B0%2C%201%5D%2C%20where%200%20means%20no%20evil%20and%201%20is%20maximum%20possible%20evil.%20If%20you%20find%20it%20difficult%20to%20imagine%20what%201%20means%2C%20look%20around%20the%20world.%20You%20will%20not%20have%20to%20imagine%3B%20you%20will%20find%20empirical%20examples.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20leader%20has%20to%20choose%20%3Cspan%3E%E2%81%A0e%20%E2%88%88%20%5B0%2C%201%5D%3C%2Fspan%3E%2C%20where%20%3Cem%3Ee%3C%2Fem%3E%20represents%20the%20extent%20of%20evil%20they%20indulge%20in%20in%20order%20to%20stay%20in%20power.%20Suppose%20for%20simplicity%20that%20the%20probability%20of%20staying%20in%20power%20for%20another%20term%20is%20equal%20to%20the%20chosen%20%3Cem%3Ee%3C%2Fem%3E.%20The%20more%20evil%20you%20do%20the%20more%20likely%20you%20are%20to%20stay%20in%20power.%20Also%20assume%2C%20once%20one%20exits%20office%2C%20one%20does%20not%20return%20again.%20This%20simplifies%20the%20analysis.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELet%20the%20joy%20or%20payoff%20of%20being%20in%20power%20for%20one%20term%20be%20denoted%20by%20x%20and%20the%20payoff%20of%20being%20out%20of%20power%20be%20y.%20Assume%20x%20%3E%20y.%3Cem%3E%20%5Bsee%20footnote%202%5D%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFew%20like%20to%20do%20evil.%20Let%20the%20guilt%20and%20remorse%20of%20doing%20evil%2C%20e%2C%20be%20given%20by%20r(e)%2C%20where%20r%E2%80%99(e)%20%3E%200%2C%20all%20e.%3Cspan%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%20%3Cem%3E%5Bsee%20footnote%203%5D%3C%2Fem%3E%20Finally%2C%20I%20assume%20r%E2%80%9D(e)%20%3E%200%20and%20r(1)%20%3E%20x%20and%20r%E2%80%B2(0)%20%26lt%3B%20x%E2%80%93y.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECondition%201%20is%20made%20simply%20to%20ensure%20that%20there%20is%20an%20interior%20solution.%20I%20will%20work%20with%20y%20%3E%200%20but%20this%20is%20not%20necessary.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20seems%20likely%20the%20politician%2C%20trying%20to%20decide%20whether%20to%20stay%20on%20in%20office%20for%20another%20term%2C%20will%20do%20the%20following%20optimization.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20will%20try%20to%20choose%20e%20to%20maximize%3A%20%CF%80%20%E2%89%A1%20xe%20%2B%20y%20(1%20%E2%88%92%20e)%20%E2%88%92%20r(e).%20(2)%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHence%2C%20e%20is%20derived%20from%20the%20first-order%20condition%20of%20maximizing%20%CF%80%3A%20(x%20%E2%88%92%20y)%20%3D%20r%E2%80%B2(e).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFigure%201%20illustrates%20this%20maximization%20exercise%2C%20with%20the%20equilibrium%20choice%20of%20evil%2C%20e%E2%88%97.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20984px)%2061vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2045vw%2C%20600px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F19145928%2Fimage-1987.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22792%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F19145928%2Fimage-1987.png%20477w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F19145928%2Fimage-1987-300x189.png%20300w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-702355%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22500%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20line%20yP%20depicts%20xe%20%2B%20y(1%20%E2%80%93%20e)%3B%20and%20the%20r(e)%20graph%20is%20also%20shown%20in%20the%20figure.%20The%20politician%20wants%20to%20maximize%20the%20gap%20between%20the%20two%2C%20described%20by%20(2).%20This%20happens%20at%20e%E2%88%97.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENote%20that%20(1)%20implies%20that%20e%E2%88%97%20%3E%200.%20Hence%2C%20this%20level%20of%20evil%20causes%20remorse%20given%20by%20r(e%E2%88%97)%2C%20which%20is%20greater%20than%200%20and%20is%20shown%20in%20the%20picture%20by%20Be%E2%88%97.%20However%2C%20it%20has%20a%20net%20benefit%20of%20AB.%20AB%20is%20the%20largest%20gap%20between%20the%20line%20yP%20and%20curve%20r(e).%20Hence%2C%20AB%20is%20greater%20than%20y%2C%20shown%20in%20the%20figure%20by%20the%20line%20segment%20y0.%20This%20means%20that%20indulging%20in%20no%20evil%2C%20that%20is%20e%20%3D%200%2C%20lowers%20the%20cost%20of%20remorse%20to%200%2C%20but%20you%20lose%20power%20for%20sure%20after%20one%20term%20and%20that%20is%20not%20attractive.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20is%2C%20however%2C%20a%20%E2%80%98mistake%E2%80%99%20the%20leader%20makes%20here%2C%20which%20is%20common%20and%20natural.%20That%20is%20the%20mistake%20of%20not%20being%20far-sighted%20enough.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETypically%2C%20if%20you%20indulge%20in%20evil%20and%20stay%20in%20power%2C%20your%20cost%20of%20exit%20in%20the%20next%20period%20will%20rise.%20That%20is%2C%20in%20the%20next%20period%2C%20the%20payoff%20from%20exiting%20from%20power%20(that%20is%2C%20the%20y%20of%20the%20next%20period)%20will%20be%20lower.%20There%20will%20be%20inquiries%20about%20why%20you%2C%20as%20president%20or%20prime%20minister%2C%20indulged%20in%20unlawful%2C%20evil%20acts%3F%20There%20may%20be%20cases%20brought%20against%20you%3B%20and%20you%20may%20even%20be%20incarcerated.%20This%20has%20happened%20to%20leaders%20in%20history.%20The%20fear%20of%20this%20must%20stalk%20Bolsonaro%2C%20Erdogan%2C%20Lukashenko%2C%20Orban%2C%20Ortega%20and%20Putin%20%E2%80%93%20presented%2C%20I%20hasten%20to%20add%2C%20in%20alphabetical%20order.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETo%20understand%20this%2C%20note%20that%20the%20above%20analysis%20was%20done%20assuming%20that%20life%20(in%20politics)%20consists%20of%20two%20(potential)%20terms%2C%20which%20means%20there%20is%20only%20one%20decision%20point%20which%20is%20the%20first%20term.%20This%20is%20because%20there%20is%20no%20decision%20to%20be%20taken%20in%20the%20final%20term%2C%20since%20in%20this%20model%20the%20only%20decision%20concerns%20how%20much%20effort%20you%20are%20willing%20to%20spend%20for%20one%20more%20term%20in%20office.%20In%20life%E2%80%99s%20last%20term%2C%20that%20decision%20does%20not%20arise.%20To%20put%20it%20another%20way%2C%20in%20the%20last%20term%2C%20you%20will%20mechanically%20choose%20e%E2%80%89%3D%E2%80%890.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENow%20think%20of%20the%20problem%20more%20generally%20as%20consisting%20of%20T-terms%2C%20where%20%3Cem%3ET%E2%80%89%3E%E2%80%891%3C%2Fem%3E.%20The%20leader%20has%20to%20take%20a%20decision%20in%20T-1%20terms%2C%20that%20is%2C%20in%20all%20but%20the%20last%20term.%20The%20dynamically%20inconsistent%20person%2C%20which%20is%20the%20way%20most%20human%20beings%20are%2C%20treats%20each%20decision%2C%20without%20detailed%20calculation%20of%20the%20full%20future.%20If%20the%20leader%20thought%20of%20the%20full%20life%E2%80%99s%20decisions%20as%20one%20big%20optimization%20problem%2C%20the%20calculation%20would%20be%20different.%20At%20each%20period%2C%20she%20would%20have%20to%20recognize%20the%20next%20period%E2%80%99s%20payoff%20from%20exiting%20from%20office%20is%20a%20decreasing%20function%20of%20the%20level%20of%20e%20chosen%20in%20this%20period.%20If%20in%20period%20%3Cem%3Et%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20the%20leader%20chooses%20evil%20%3Cem%3Ee%3Csub%3Et%3C%2Fsub%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%20and%20the%20payoff%20from%20leaving%20power%20in%20the%20next%20period%20is%20%3Cem%3Ey%3Csub%3Et%E2%80%89%2B%E2%80%891%3C%2Fsub%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20what%20I%20am%20asserting%20is%20that%20%3Cem%3E%5Bsee%20footnote%204%5D%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cspan%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3Ey%20t%2B1%20%3D%20f%20(e%20t)%20%2C%20f%20%E2%80%B2%20(e%20t)%20%26lt%3B%200.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIf%20we%20denote%20the%20net%20payoff%20in%20each%20period%2C%20t%2C%20by%20%CF%80t%2C%20which%20is%20defined%20the%20same%20way%20as%20(1)%2C%20above%2C%20then%20the%20full%20optimization%20exercise%20consists%20of%20choosing%20(e1%20%2C%20e2%20%2C%20.%20.%20.%20e%20T%E2%88%921)%20to%20maximize%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%CF%801%20%2B%20%CF%802%20%2B%20%C2%B7%20%C2%B7%20%C2%B7%20%2B%20%CF%80T%E2%88%921%20.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20main%20theorem%20is%20the%20following%3A%20There%20exist%20parameters%2C%20under%20which%2C%20if%20this%20full%20optimization%20is%20done%2C%20the%20political%20leader%20will%20choose%20e%20t%20%3D%200%2C%20for%20all%20t.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20if%20the%20choice%20is%20made%20in%20each%20period%2C%20unmindful%20of%20the%20fact%20that%20this%20term%E2%80%99s%20choice%20of%20e%2C%20will%20have%20an%20effect%20on%20next%20term%E2%80%99s%20value%20of%20y%2C%20or%20treating%20this%20term%20and%20the%20next%20term%20as%20the%20only%20two%20terms%20of%20life%2C%20then%20the%20politician%20will%20choose%20(e1%20%2C%20e2%20%2C%20.%20.%20.%20e%20T%E2%88%921)%20such%20that%20e1%20%26lt%3B%20e2%20%26lt%3B%20%C2%B7%20%C2%B7%20%C2%B7%20%26lt%3B%20e%20T%E2%88%921..%20That%20is%2C%20the%20extent%20of%20evil%20actions%20chosen%20will%20increase%20monotonically%20with%20each%20term%20in%20office.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20process%20of%20morphing%20into%20a%20tyrant%20is%20inexorable.%20The%20consequence%20of%20the%20cost%20of%20exit%20getting%20higher%20in%20each%20term%20is%20that%20you%20will%20have%20to%20indulge%20in%20even%20greater%20political%20intrigue%2C%20ruthlessness%20and%20evil%20to%20make%20sure%20you%20do%20not%20get%20thrown%20out%20of%20office.%20The%20following%20period%20you%20have%20to%20do%20even%20more.%20Ultimately%2C%20you%20morph%20into%20late%20stage%20Alexander%20Lukashenko%2C%20Vladimir%20Putin%20or%20Daniel%20Ortega.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIf%20they%20knew%20how%20to%20do%20dynamic%20programming%20right%2C%20they%20may%20not%20have%20got%20into%20the%20process%20at%20the%20start%2C%20done%20one%20good%20term%20in%20office%20and%20left.%20But%20this%20kind%20of%20short-sightedness%2C%20whether%20we%20call%20it%20hyperbolic%20discounting%20or%20just%20unawareness%20of%20the%20full%20impact%20of%20your%20action%20into%20the%20future%2C%20is%20a%20common%20human%20mistake.%20The%20problem%20is%20that%20this%20has%20devastating%20consequences%20for%20the%20well-being%20of%20society%20and%20the%20world%2C%20as%20we%20can%20see%20from%20the%20Ukraine%20war.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOne%20can%20give%20a%20formal%20proof%20of%20the%20theorem%20for%20the%20T-period%20game%20by%20solving%20the%20full%20optimization.%20But%20the%20intuition%20is%20easy%20enough%20that%20the%20algebra%20is%20redundant.%20I%20give%20a%20proof%20here%20for%20the%20case%20where%20T%20%3D%203%3B%20so%20that%20there%20are%20two%20decision%20points.%20The%20entire%20proof%20is%20obvious%20using%20one%20diagram%2C%20Figure%202.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20496px)%2085vw%2C%20496px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F19150715%2Fimage-1988.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22496%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F19150715%2Fimage-1988.png%20496w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F19150715%2Fimage-1988-300x183.png%20300w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-702362%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22302%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20part%20of%20Fig.%202%20is%20a%20reproduction%20of%20Fig.%201%2C%20where%20the%20leader%20chose%20e%E2%88%97%20in%20period%201%2C%20when%20the%20exit%20option%20was%20y%2C%20where%20y%20%3D%20f(0)%2C%20since%20at%20the%20start%20there%20is%20no%20history%20of%20evil.%20Denote%20f(e%E2%88%97)%20by%20y%E2%80%99.%20We%20know%20that%20y%E2%80%99%20%26lt%3B%20y%2C%20since%20f%E2%80%99%20%26lt%3B%200.%20It%20is%20easy%20to%20see%20that%20as%20y%20falls%2C%20the%20line%20yP%20becomes%20steeper%20by%20pivoting%20around%20point%20P.%20This%20is%20because%2C%20as%20one%20can%20see%20from%20(1)%2C%20at%20e%20%3D%201%2C%20%CF%80%20is%20independent%20of%20y.%20Hence%2C%20as%20y%20falls%20to%20y%E2%80%99%2C%20the%20earlier%20line%2C%20yP%2C%20pivots%20at%20P%20and%20become%20y%E2%80%99P.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIf%20we%20now%20denote%20the%20optimal%20choice%20of%20e%20by%20e%E2%80%99%2C%20it%20must%20be%20that%20e%E2%80%99%20%3E%20e%E2%88%97%2C%20since%20r%E2%80%9D(e)%20%3E%200.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENow%20it%20is%20entirely%20possible%20to%20think%20of%20parameters%20such%20that%2C%20the%20leader%2C%20if%20she%20did%20the%20full%20optimization%20for%20the%20three-term%20game%2C%20she%20would%20prefer%20to%20choose%20e%20%3D%200%20in%20both%20decision%20points%20(that%20is%2C%20in%20terms%201%20and%202)%2C%20rather%20than%20choosing%20e%E2%88%97%20and%20e%E2%80%99%20as%20he%20does%20when%20he%20is%20short-sighted%20and%20ignores%20the%20effect%20on%20his%20exit%20option%20when%20he%20chooses%202.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETo%20see%20this%2C%20note%20that%2C%20if%20she%20chooses%20e%20%3D%200%20in%20both%20the%20first%20term%20and%20the%20second%20term%2C%20the%20total%20benefit%20he%20gets%20over%20time%20is%20x%20%2B%20y%20%2B%20y.%20This%20is%20because%2C%20in%20term%201%2C%20she%20is%20in%20office%20and%20so%20gets%20x.%20Since%20she%20chooses%20e%20%3D%200%2C%20in%20term1%2C%20she%20incurs%20no%20remorse%20from%20choosing%20evil%20but%20she%20has%20to%20leave%20office%20and%20so%20gets%20y.%20Once%20out%20of%20office%2C%20always%20out%20of%20office%3B%20so%20in%20term%203%20she%20again%20gets%20y.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENext%20suppose%20he%20chooses%20e%E2%88%97%20and%20e%E2%80%99%20in%20term%201%20and%20term%202.%20The%20total%20payoff%20she%20gets%20over%20time%20is%20x%20%2B%20AB%20%2B%20(1%20%E2%80%93%20e%E2%88%97)%20y%20%2B%20e%E2%88%97CD%2C%20where%20the%20AB%20and%20CD%20refer%20to%20the%20line%20segments%20in%20Fig.%202.%20This%20is%20easy%20to%20see.%20In%20term%201%2C%20she%20is%20already%20in%20office%20and%20gets%20x.%20By%20choosing%20e%E2%88%97%20in%20term%202%2C%20she%20gets%20AB.%20But%20choosing%20e%E2%88%97%20means%20she%20has%20a%20probability%20(1-e%E2%88%97)%20of%20losing%20power%2C%20in%20which%20case%20she%20gets%20y%20or%20probability%20e%E2%88%97%20of%20staying%20in%20power%2C%20in%20which%20case%20she%20gets%20an%20expected%20payoff%20of%20CD.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAll%20we%20need%20to%20show%20is%20that%20it%20is%20possible%20that%3A%20x%20%2B%20y%20%2B%20y%20%3E%20x%20%2B%20AB%2B%20(1%20%E2%80%93%20e%E2%88%97)%20y%20%2B%20e%E2%88%97CD.%20In%20other%20words%2C%20we%20have%20to%20show%3A%20(1%20%2B%20e%E2%88%97)y%20%3E%20AB%20%2B%20e%E2%88%97CD.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFrom%20the%20fact%20of%20the%20leader%E2%80%99s%20optimization%2C%20we%20know%20that%20in%20Fig.%202%2C%20AB%20is%20greater%20than%20both%20y%20and%20CD.%20But%20this%20is%20compatible%20with%20y%20being%20close%20to%20AB%20and%20CD%20being%20much%20smaller%20than%20y%2C%20which%20would%20make%20the%20above%20inequality%20valid.%20This%20completes%20the%20proof.%20It%20is%20intuitively%20obvious%20that%2C%20in%20the%20general%20case%2C%20with%20T%20%3E%202%2C%20even%20if%20a%20leader%20does%20the%20optimization%20for%20a%20few%20periods%20into%20the%20future%20at%20a%20time%20(instead%20of%20just%20one%20period%20at%20a%20time%2C%20as%20in%20the%20above%20example)%2C%20but%20not%20the%20whole%20length%20of%20the%20future%2C%20she%20could%20end%20up%20on%20a%20path%20where%20she%20has%20to%20indulge%20in%20increasing%20evil%20acts%20to%20stay%20in%20power%2C%20morphing%20fully%20into%20a%20tyrant%20after%20some%20stretch%20of%20time%20in%20office.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBefore%20commenting%20on%20the%20normative%20and%20policy%20implications%20of%20the%20above%20claim%2C%20I%20want%20to%20add%20a%20few%20technical%20comments%20and%20caveats.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFirst%2C%20note%20that%20some%20neoclassical%20economists%20assume%20people%20are%20always%20rational%20and%20so%20they%20reject%20some%20of%20the%20premises%20of%20behavioral%20economics.%20At%20times%20this%20becomes%20a%20tautology.%20They%20assume%20people%20are%20always%20rational%20and%2C%20no%20matter%20how%20they%20behave%2C%20they%20describe%20this%20as%20rational%20behavior.%20This%20leads%20to%20contortions%20of%20the%20model%20to%20ensure%20that%20dynamic%20inconsistency%2C%20which%20implies%20a%20form%20of%20intransitivity%20of%20preference%2C%20cannot%20occur%2C%20by%20definition.%20Interestingly%2C%20there%20is%20work%20in%20philosophy%20(see%20Parfit%2C%201984)%2C%20that%20asserts%20how%2C%20especially%20in%20domains%20of%20moral%20decision-making%2C%20people%20may%20be%20fully%20rational%20and%20violate%20transitivity.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETaking%20cue%20from%20this%2C%20we%20can%20create%20models%20where%20dynamic%20inconsistency%20is%20compatible%20with%20rational%20behavior.%20That%20is%2C%20it%20is%20possible%20to%20conceive%20of%20contexts%20where%20there%20is%20a%20set%20of%20decisions%20to%20be%20taken%20over%20time%2C%20each%20decision%20is%20taken%20fully%20rationally%2C%20but%20at%20the%20end%20of%20it%20all%2C%20the%20individual%20has%20reason%20to%20regret%20the%20choices.%20This%20is%20possible%20in%20contexts%20where%20there%20is%20an%20infinite%20number%20of%20decision%20points%20%3Cem%3E%5Bsee%20footnote%205%5D%3C%2Fem%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20present%20context%2C%20if%20we%20assume%20that%20this%20is%20an%20infinite%20decision%20problem%2C%20that%20is%2C%20during%20a%20politician%E2%80%99s%20lifetime%2C%20there%20are%20an%20infinite%20number%20of%20occasions%20where%20she%20can%20decide%20what%20to%20do%20to%20enhance%20her%20political%20power%2C%20we%20can%20create%20a%20game%20akin%20to%20some%20of%20the%20art%20of%20M.%20C.%20Escher%2C%20where%20each%20step%20enhances%20the%20players%20utility%2C%20but%20the%20player%20ends%20up%20with%20a%20utility%20level%2C%20below%20where%20she%20had%20started.%20I%20argued%20elsewhere%20(Basu%2C%201994)%2C%20this%20can%20happen%20not%20just%20in%20art%2C%20but%20in%20games.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESecond%2C%20the%20above%20model%20showing%20the%20morphing%20of%20tyrants%20was%20presented%20using%20many%20strong%20assumptions.%20The%20reason%20is%20that%20my%20claim%20is%20not%20that%20the%20morphing%20will%20always%20happen%2C%20which%20would%20require%20proving%20it%20under%20the%20most%20general%20conditions%2C%20but%20that%20there%20is%20a%20propensity%20for%20this%20to%20happen%20under%20reasonable%20situations.%20However%2C%20it%20is%20worth%20pointing%20out%20that%20many%20of%20the%20assumptions%20can%20be%20relaxed%20without%20losing%20the%20result.%20For%20instance%2C%20the%20assumption%20that%20the%20function%20r(e)%20is%20increasing%20and%20convex%20can%20be%20generalized%20if%20we%20relax%20the%20assumption%20that%20the%20probability%20of%20winning%20another%20term%20is%20equal%20to%20e%2C%20as%20assumed%20in%20the%20above%20model.%20Allowing%20for%20non-linearity%20in%20this%20will%20allow%20us%20to%20relax%20some%20of%20the%20restrictions%20on%20r(e)%20and%20to%20get%20the%20same%20result.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThird%2C%20the%20fact%20that%20it%20was%20assumed%20that%20it%20is%20political%20intrigue%20and%20evil%2C%20variable%20e%20in%20the%20model%2C%20that%20helps%20authoritarian%20leaders%20to%20prolong%20their%20hold%20on%20power%2C%20may%20suggest%20that%20it%20is%20being%20assumed%20that%20doing%20good%20does%20not%20help%20retain%20power.%20That%20is%20not%20however%20an%20assumption%20being%20made%20here.%20In%20fact%2C%20doing%20good%2C%20or%20at%20least%20doing%20visible%20good%2C%20will%20typically%20help%20prolong%20a%20leader%E2%80%99s%20term%20in%20office.%20However%2C%20that%20is%20a%20tactic%20that%20all%20leaders%20will%20use%20because%20doing%20good%20will%20make%20them%20feel%20good%20and%20help%20society.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHence%2C%20this%20is%20a%20strategy%20that%20will%20be%20used%20by%20all.%20The%20interesting%20challenge%20arises%20when%20this%20strategy%20is%20exhausted%20and%20the%20leader%20has%20to%20choose%20e%2C%20and%20hence%20that%20is%20what%20the%20model%20focusses%20on.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFinally%2C%20there%20is%20one%20important%20assumption%20used%20in%20the%20paper%20that%20may%20be%20worth%20trying%20to%20generalise%20in%20the%20future.%20Note%20that%20in%20the%20above%20model%20it%20is%20assumed%20that%20the%20leader%20chooses%20e%2C%20keeping%20in%20mind%20that%20the%20payoff%20of%20failing%20to%20remain%20in%20office%20is%20given%20by%20y.%20In%20reality%2C%20the%20y%20will%20itself%20depend%20on%20the%20e%2C%20and%20as%20e%20increases%2C%20y%20will%20fall%2C%20that%20is%2C%20the%20exit%20option%20for%20the%20dictator%20will%20get%20worse.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELeaders%20with%20a%20little%20far-sightedness%2C%20even%20if%20they%20are%20not%20doing%20the%20full%20optimization%20over%20time%2C%20should%20be%20aware%20of%20this.%20This%20injection%20of%20reality%20will%20complicate%20the%20model.%20However%2C%20if%20we%20assume%20that%20y%20depends%20on%20the%20accumulated%20evil%20indulged%20by%20the%20leader%20in%20the%20previous%20terms%20in%20office%2C%20plus%20the%20evil%20done%20now%2C%20that%20is%2C%20e%2C%20to%20stay%20in%20office%20for%20another%20term%2C%20it%20should%20be%20possible%20to%20build%20a%20more%20sophisticated%20model%20which%20will%20continue%20to%20give%20a%20result%20similar%20to%20the%20one%20obtained%20in%20the%20present%20paper.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ESome%20normative%20questions%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20paper%20is%20part%20of%20a%20larger%20discourse%20on%20the%20power%20of%20the%20leader%20or%20the%20state%2C%20and%20the%20risk%20of%20oppression%20and%20violation%20of%20basic%20human%20rights%20of%20individuals%20that%20goes%20back%20to%20the%2017th%20century%2C%20but%20has%20been%20a%20topic%20of%20contemporary%20interest%2C%20as%20part%20of%20a%20larger%20discourse%20on%20collective%20action%20and%20power%20(%3Cspan%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20data-open%3D%5C%22ref22%5C%22%20data-google-interstitial%3D%5C%22false%5C%22%3EHobbes%2C%201651%3C%2Fa%3E%3B%20%3Cspan%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20data-open%3D%5C%22ref20%5C%22%20data-google-interstitial%3D%5C%22false%5C%22%3EAcemoglu%20and%20Robinson%2C%202019%3C%2Fa%3E%3B%20%3Cspan%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20data-open%3D%5C%22ref10%5C%22%20data-google-interstitial%3D%5C%22false%5C%22%3EBinmore%2C%202020%3C%2Fa%3E%3B%20%3Cspan%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20data-open%3D%5C%22ref19%5C%22%20data-google-interstitial%3D%5C%22false%5C%22%3EFerguson%2C%202020%3C%2Fa%3E%3B%20%3Cspan%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20data-open%3D%5C%22ref26%5C%22%20data-google-interstitial%3D%5C%22false%5C%22%3ELopez-Calva%20and%20Bolch%2C%202022%3C%2Fa%3E%3B%20%3Cspan%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20data-open%3D%5C%22ref8%5C%22%20data-google-interstitial%3D%5C%22false%5C%22%3EBasu%2C%202022b%3C%2Fa%3E).%20It%20is%20possible%20to%20argue%20that%20leadership%20is%20often%20needed%20to%20achieve%20the%20social%20good%2C%20but%20there%20is%20always%20the%20risk%20of%20the%20leader%20going%20astray%2C%20or%20morphing%20into%20a%20force%20of%20evil%2C%20as%20the%20above%20model%20illustrates.%20Given%20this%20very%20real%20problem%20of%20political%20economy%2C%20what%20can%20we%20do%20by%20way%20of%20policy%20and%20prior%20regulation%20to%20prevent%20such%20a%20predicament%3F%20How%20do%20we%20put%20checks%20and%20balances%20on%20the%20leader%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMost%20problems%20of%20political%20economy%20are%20unlikely%20to%20be%20fully%20solvable.%20This%20is%20because%2C%20in%20reality%2C%20there%20is%20no%20such%20thing%20as%20the%20ultimate%20game%20of%20life.%20As%20you%20devise%20rules%20to%20prevent%20people%20or%20players%20from%20indulging%20in%20bad%20behavior%2C%20they%20can%20keep%20finding%20new%20strategies%2C%20beyond%20the%20original%20game%20of%20life%20%3Cem%3E%5Bsee%20footnote%206%5D%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20to%20perpetrate%20evil.%20The%20only%20hope%20for%20well-meaning%20policymakers%20is%20to%20try%20to%20stay%20ahead%20of%20the%20curve.%20It%20is%20in%20this%20spirit%20that%20I%20offer%20some%20closing%20comments%2C%20aware%20that%20they%20raise%20more%20questions%20than%20answers.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAt%20this%20time%2C%20what%20the%20above%20theoretical%20model%20points%20to%20is%20the%20need%20for%20%3Cem%3Eex%20ante%3C%2Fem%3E%20agreements%2C%20akin%20to%20constitutions%2C%20which%20debar%20certain%20kinds%20of%20actions%20by%20human%20beings.%20The%20key%20is%20to%20have%20agreements%20in%20advance%20which%20deter%20certain%20behaviors%20in%20the%20future.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhy%20would%20such%20agreements%20work%3F%20One%20reason%2C%20rooted%20in%20economics%20and%20game%20theory%20but%20not%20widely%20understood%2C%20is%20that%20the%20social%2C%20political%20and%20economic%20world%20we%20inhabit%20has%20multiple%20equilibria.%20Prior%20agreements%20are%20ways%20of%20nudging%20ourselves%20away%20from%20the%20current%20equilibrium%20to%20another%20collectively%20more%20desirable%20equilibrium.%20The%20key%20word%20here%20is%20%E2%80%98equilibrium%E2%80%99.%20If%20this%20is%20done%20successfully%2C%20the%20question%20of%20why%20people%20will%20adhere%20to%20a%20constitution%20is%20easy%20to%20answer.%20If%20the%20constitution%20is%20a%20set%20of%20rules%20which%20has%20the%20property%20of%20constituting%20an%20equilibrium%2C%20then%20once%20it%20becomes%20focal%20it%20will%20be%20adhered%20to%20simply%20because%20it%20is%20in%20each%20person%E2%80%99s%20self-interest%20to%20abide%20by%20the%20constitution%20if%20others%20abide%20by%20the%20constitution.%20I%20am%20using%20the%20term%20%E2%80%98equilibrium%E2%80%99%20in%20a%20somewhat%20unconventional%20way%2C%20to%20denote%20a%20stable%20vector%20of%20sets%20of%20omitted%20strategies.%20Each%20player%20agrees%20not%20to%20use%20certain%20strategies%20if%20other%20players%20agree%20not%20to%20use%20some%20of%20their%20strategies%20%3Cem%3E%5Bsee%20footnote%207%5D%3C%2Fem%3E.%3Csup%3E%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fsup%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBy%20this%20criterion%20the%20challenge%20is%20to%20draft%20a%20constitution%20that%20happens%20to%20be%20one%20of%20the%20equilibria%20of%20this%20society%20and%20then%20create%20pressures%20so%20that%20this%20equilibrium%20becomes%20a%20focal%20point%20to%20which%20people%20are%20willing%20to%20shift.%20Further%2C%20in%20our%20globalizing%20world%20the%20need%20is%20for%20a%20global%20constitution%20and%20global%20agreements.%20Globalization%20raises%20important%20questions%20of%20global%20justice%20(%3Cspan%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20data-open%3D%5C%22ref21%5C%22%20data-google-interstitial%3D%5C%22false%5C%22%3EHassoun%2C%202012%3C%2Fa%3E).%20Just%20as%20we%20have%20an%20obligation%20toward%20the%20global%20poor%2C%20we%20have%20an%20obligation%20toward%20those%20whose%20basic%20human%20rights%20are%20violated%20by%20dictators%20and%20tyrants%2C%20no%20matter%20where%20they%20live.%20We%20are%20at%20a%20stage%20of%20history%2C%20where%20we%20have%20no%20escape%20but%20to%20be%20more%20intrusive%20in%20other%20nations.%20There%20will%20have%20to%20be%20lines%2C%20which%2C%20if%20nations%20cross%20them%2C%20others%20acquire%20the%20right%20to%20intervene.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20striving%20for%20such%20agreements%20and%20constitutions%2C%20it%20is%20worth%20keeping%20in%20mind%20that%20there%20are%20other%20options%2C%20which%20require%20us%20to%20step%20beyond%20the%20conventional%20idea%20of%20equilibrium.%20The%20belief%20that%20individuals%20choose%20from%20the%20universal%20set%20of%20all%20available%20actions%2C%20and%20they%20choose%20rationally%20from%20this%20set%2C%20as%20mainstream%20economics%20assumes%2C%20is%20deeply%20flawed.%20First%20of%20all%2C%20we%20all%20have%20social%20norms%20and%20moral%20hard-wirings%20that%20we%20adhere%20to.%20What%20is%20ignored%20in%20mainstream%20neoclassical%20economics%20is%20that%20these%20moral%20and%20normative%20moorings%20are%20often%20critical%20for%20markets%20to%20function%20and%20society%20to%20prosper%20(%3Cspan%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20data-open%3D%5C%22ref6%5C%22%20data-google-interstitial%3D%5C%22false%5C%22%3EBasu%2C%202000%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Chapter%204%3B%20%3Cspan%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20data-open%3D%5C%22ref12%5C%22%20data-google-interstitial%3D%5C%22false%5C%22%3EBowles%20and%20Gintis%2C%201998%3C%2Fa%3E%3B%20%3Cspan%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20data-open%3D%5C%22ref11%5C%22%20data-google-interstitial%3D%5C%22false%5C%22%3EBowles%2C%202016%3C%2Fa%3E).%20Further%2C%20these%20norms%20may%20change%20and%20get%20modified%20over%20time%2C%20solving%20and%20occasionally%20creating%20new%20problems.%20These%20norms%20are%20often%20so%20embedded%20in%20our%20psyche%20that%20we%20abide%20by%20them%20unwittingly.%20We%20do%20not%20bite%20others%2C%20even%20when%20that%20would%20clearly%20help%20us%2C%20not%20because%20this%20action%20is%20not%20available%20in%20the%20game%20of%20life%2C%20nor%20because%20on%20doing%20cost%E2%80%93benefit%20analysis%2C%20we%20find%20this%20does%20not%20give%20us%20a%20positive%20payoff%2C%20but%20simply%20because%20our%20norms%20have%20programmed%20us%20not%20to%20even%20consider%20this%20action.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20other%20ways%20in%20which%20the%20notion%20(common%20in%20economics)%20of%20human%20beings%20having%20exogenously%20given%20preferences%20or%20payoff%20functions%2C%20has%20been%20contested.%20We%20know%2C%20for%20instance%2C%20that%20people%20often%20choose%20actions%20in%20order%20to%20enhance%20their%20self-esteem%20(see%20%3Cspan%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20data-open%3D%5C%22ref17%5C%22%20data-google-interstitial%3D%5C%22false%5C%22%3ECrocker%20and%20Wolfe%2C%202001%3C%2Fa%3E%3B%20R.%20%3Cspan%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20data-open%3D%5C%22ref3%5C%22%20data-google-interstitial%3D%5C%22false%5C%22%3EAkerlof%2C%202017b%3C%2Fa%3E).%20Moreover%2C%20there%20is%20often%20a%20tussle%20between%20self-esteem%20and%20the%20esteem%20of%20peers.%20If%20being%20in%20power%20raises%20esteem%20(of%20oneself%20or%20of%20the%20peers)%2C%20a%20political%20leader%20may%20try%20harder%20to%20stay%20in%20power.%20If%2C%20on%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20giving%20up%20power%2C%20when%20one%20could%20have%20clung%20on%20to%20it%2C%20raises%20esteem%2C%20the%20leader%20may%20be%20more%20inclined%20to%20quit%20office.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20awareness%20of%20these%20norms%20and%20endogenous%20elements%20in%20human%20preferences%20opens%20up%20a%20vast%20terrain%20of%20research%20and%20analysis%20that%20goes%20beyond%20mainstream%20economics%20and%20straddles%20the%20terrain%20between%20sociology%20and%20economics%20(%3Cspan%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20data-open%3D%5C%22ref25%5C%22%20data-google-interstitial%3D%5C%22false%5C%22%3EKliemt%2C%202020%3C%2Fa%3E%3B%20%3Cspan%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20data-open%3D%5C%22ref16%5C%22%20data-google-interstitial%3D%5C%22false%5C%22%3ECoyle%2C%202021%3C%2Fa%3E%3B%20%3Cspan%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20data-open%3D%5C%22ref7%5C%22%20data-google-interstitial%3D%5C%22false%5C%22%3EBasu%2C%202022a%3C%2Fa%3E).%20This%20can%20also%20bring%20to%20light%20new%20avenues%20for%20modifying%20our%20behavior%20in%20order%20to%20create%20a%20better%20world.%20By%20changing%20what%20we%20esteem%20in%20our%20peers%2C%20we%20can%20prompt%20our%20peers%20to%20behave%20differently.%20This%20is%20a%20matter%20of%20some%20urgency%20in%20our%20troubled%20world.%20Though%20the%20definitive%20answer%20to%20this%20may%20take%20time%20to%20evolve%2C%20it%20is%20a%20direction%20of%20research%20worth%20pursuing%20in%20the%20future.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELet%20me%20close%20by%20addressing%20a%20narrower%20matter%2C%20which%20arises%20directly%20from%20the%20above%20model.%20This%20concerns%20having%20global%20rules%20concerning%20term%20limit.%20A%20tyrannical%20leader%20in%20one%20nation%20can%20destabilize%20the%20world.%20So%2C%20ideally%2C%20we%20need%20a%20term-limit%20requirement%20built%20into%20an%20international%20charter%20or%20a%20global%20constitution.%20If%20the%20T%2C%20in%20the%20above%20game%2C%20is%20capped%20by%20a%20charter%20at%202%2C%20there%20will%20be%20only%20that%20much%20evil%20a%20leader%20can%20morph%20into.%20What%20is%20more%20important%2C%20is%20that%20leaders%2C%20being%20aware%20that%20they%20will%20%3Cem%3Ehave%20to%3C%2Fem%3E%20exit%2C%20will%20be%20more%20conscious%20of%20their%20behavior%20when%20in%20office%20%3Cem%3E%5Bsee%20footnote%208%5D%3C%2Fem%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20possible%20to%20think%20of%20more%20immediate%20actions%2C%20that%20is%2C%20even%20before%20a%20global%20agreement%20is%20reached.%20For%20this%2C%20we%20have%20to%20get%20away%20from%20our%20propensity%20to%20think%20of%20nations%20as%20individuals%20or%20players.%20Thus%20the%20Cuban%20missile%20crisis%20is%20typically%20modeled%20as%20a%20two-player%20game%2C%20USA%20and%20USSR%20locked%20in%20a%20deadly%20Hawk-Dove%20scenario.%20Likewise%2C%20there%20is%20a%20body%20of%20writing%20on%20the%20war%20games%20in%20the%20Korean%20Peninsula%20and%20what%20we%20can%20do%20to%20avert%20disaster.%20This%20is%20conducted%20mostly%20in%20terms%20of%20a%20game%20between%20North%20Korea%2C%20USA%2C%20China%20and%20Russia%2C%20occasionally%20tossing%20in%20South%20Korea.%20Much%20of%20this%20is%20done%20again%20treating%20nations%20as%20players.%20When%20individuals%20are%20brought%20in%2C%20like%20Kim%20Jong-un%2C%20they%20are%20treated%20as%20having%20interests%20totally%20aligned%20with%20their%20own%20nation%20%E2%80%93%20%E2%80%98Kim%20Jong-un%20is%20an%20ardent%20nationalist%20who%20regularly%20responds%20to%20threats%20by%20upping%20the%20ante%E2%80%99%20(%3Cspan%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20data-open%3D%5C%22ref27%5C%22%20data-google-interstitial%3D%5C%22false%5C%22%3EMenon%2C%202017%3C%2Fa%3E).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhat%20is%20not%20always%20recognized%20in%20popular%20discourse%20but%20is%20a%20central%20tenet%20of%20modern%20political%20economy%2C%20at%20least%20since%20the%20seminal%20work%20of%20%3Cspan%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20data-open%3D%5C%22ref18%5C%22%20data-google-interstitial%3D%5C%22false%5C%22%3EDowns%20(1957)%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20is%20that%20leaders%20have%20their%20own%20interests%2C%20which%20are%20not%20aligned%20with%20the%20interest%20of%20the%20nation.%20Many%20dictators%20who%20have%20long%20been%20in%20power%20may%20want%20to%20exit%20purely%20for%20their%20own%20interest%2C%20but%20they%20may%20not%20have%20a%20viable%20exit%20option%20%3Cem%3E%5Bsee%20footnote%209%5D%3C%2Fem%3E.%20They%20know%20that%2C%20once%20out%20of%20power%2C%20they%20will%20be%20punished%20by%20their%20own%20people%20or%20even%20killed%20by%20the%20generals.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20not%20immediately%20clear%20how%20to%20solve%20this.%20Some%20may%20argue%20that%20the%20way%20to%20solve%20this%20is%20to%20create%20attractive%20exit%20options.%20This%20would%20amount%20to%20the%20US%20telling%20Kim%20Jong-un%2C%20%E2%80%98If%20you%20stop%20oppressing%20your%20people%20and%20threatening%20other%20nations%2C%20we%20will%20protect%20you%20by%20helping%20you%20leave%20your%20country%2C%20and%20give%20you%20a%20castle%20on%20a%20pacific%20island%20to%20settle%20in.%E2%80%99%20This%20could%20help%20us%20deal%20with%20Kim%20Jong-un%20and%20promote%20peace%20in%20his%20nation%20and%20the%20world.%20But%20no%20problem%20in%20economics%20comes%20with%20the%20absolute%20final%20answer.%20If%20the%20US%20uses%20this%20strategy%20regularly%20for%20world%20peace%2C%20we%20will%20have%20another%20problem.%20Individuals%20with%20no%20interest%20in%20power%20and%20tyranny%20may%20now%20strive%20to%20become%20tyrants%20for%20no%20other%20reason%20but%20to%20get%20that%20castle%20in%20the%20Pacific%20Island.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EAcknowledgment%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20paper%20began%20with%20a%20presentation%20at%20the%20Fifth%20Conference%20of%20Philosophy%2C%20Politics%20%26amp%3B%20Economics%20(PPE)%20Society%2C%20New%20Orleans%2C%203%E2%80%935%20February%202022%2C%20and%20was%20developed%20further%20as%20part%20of%20my%20W.%20Edmond%20Clark%20Distinguished%20Lecture%20at%20Queen%E2%80%99s%20University%2C%20Canada%2C%20delivered%20on%206%20April%202022.%20The%20nudge%20to%20bring%20the%20paper%20to%20closure%20needed%20the%20free-flowing%20conversation%20I%20had%20with%20Hartmut%20Kliemt.%20%3Cem%3EEn%20route%3C%2Fem%3E%20to%20completing%20the%20paper%2C%20I%20had%20conversations%20with%20and%20received%20comments%20from%20many.%20I%20owe%20special%20thanks%20to%20George%20Akerlof%2C%20Nancy%20Chau%2C%20Chris%20Cotton%2C%20Joe%20Halpern%2C%20Nicole%20Hassoun%2C%20Chenyang%20Li%2C%20Hans-Bernd%20Sch%C3%A4fer%2C%20Arunava%20Sen%20and%20Saloni%20Vadeyar.%20I%20want%20to%20thank%20the%20Bucerius%20Law%20School%2C%20Hamburg%2C%20for%20hosting%20me%20during%20the%20last%20lap%20of%20work%20and%20Cornell%20University%E2%80%99s%20Microeconomic%20Theory%20workshop%20where%20I%20presented%20the%20paper.%20Finally%2C%20I%20would%20like%20to%20thank%20two%20anonymous%20referees%20of%20the%20journal%20for%20valuable%20comments%2C%20many%20of%20which%20are%20now%20part%20of%20the%20text.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EFootnotes%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cspan%20data-fn-id%3D%5C%22fn1%5C%22%3E1.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fspan%3EIt%20is%20also%20possible%20that%20as%20people%20indulge%20in%20such%20acts%20they%20internalize%20these%20as%20not%20evil%20acts%20but%20hard%20decisions%20one%20has%20to%20make%20for%20the%20good%20of%20the%20nation.%20Such%20delusions%20make%20it%20easier%20to%20live%20with%20oneself.%20Their%20persistence%20is%20also%20made%20more%20likely%20by%20the%20advisers%20who%20surround%20the%20leader%20and%20misinform%20and%20help%20create%20such%20a%20make%20belief%20world.%20For%20simplicity%20of%20analysis%2C%20I%20shall%20stay%20away%20from%20these%20complexities.%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cspan%20data-fn-id%3D%5C%22fn2%5C%22%3E2.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fspan%3EThe%20constituents%20of%20the%20joy%20of%20being%20in%20office%20are%20not%20modeled%20here.%20One%20joy%20could%20come%20from%20being%20able%20to%20do%20what%20you%20believe%20is%20good%20for%20the%20nation.%20The%20reason%20why%20you%20may%20be%20able%20to%20do%20good%20in%20office%20is%20that%20being%20in%20office%20is%20a%20way%20to%20get%20legitimacy%20over%20others.%20You%20can%20simply%20give%20orders%20to%20incentivize%20others%20(%3Cspan%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20data-open%3D%5C%22ref2%5C%22%20data-google-interstitial%3D%5C%22false%5C%22%3EAkerlof%2C%202017a%3C%2Fa%3E).%20This%20is%20what%20leaders%20do%20and%20it%20is%20not%20hard%20to%20model%20this%20(%3Cspan%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20data-open%3D%5C%22ref8%5C%22%20data-google-interstitial%3D%5C%22false%5C%22%3EBasu%2C%202022b%3C%2Fa%3E).%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cspan%20data-fn-id%3D%5C%22fn3%5C%22%3E3.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fspan%3EIt%20is%20possible%20that%20some%20of%20the%20power-hungry%20leaders%2C%20feel%20no%20remorse%20or%20guilt.%20That%20will%20simply%20reinforce%20the%20result.%20What%20makes%20the%20result%20obtained%20in%20this%20paper%20more%20interesting%20is%20that%20it%20survives%20even%20if%20the%20leader%20does%20have%20guilt-feeling.%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cspan%20data-fn-id%3D%5C%22fn4%5C%22%3E4%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fspan%3EThe%20assumption%20that%20the%20cost%20of%20evil%20acts%20upon%20exit%20from%20office%20happens%20in%20the%20next%20period%20is%20made%20for%20algebraic%20simplicity.%20It%20is%20arguable%20if%20one%20acts%20evil%20and%20fails%20to%20remain%20in%20power%20one%20will%20have%20to%20pay%20for%20the%20evil%20right%20away.%20This%20will%20yield%20the%20same%20result%20as%20in%20the%20paper%20if%20we%20make%20the%20payoff%20upon%20exit%20to%20depend%20on%20the%20accumulation%20of%20all%20past%20terms%20in%20office%20including%20the%20immediate%20one.%20In%20other%20words%2C%20we%20could%20assume%2C%20y%20t%20%3D%20f%20(e1%20%2B%20e2%20%2B%20.%20.%20.%20e%20t)%20%2C%20where%20f%20%E2%80%B2%20%26lt%3B%200.%20We%20would%20end%20up%20with%20a%20little%20more%20algebra%20and%20the%20same%20result.%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cspan%20data-fn-id%3D%5C%22fn5%5C%22%3E5.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fspan%3EThere%20is%20a%20literature%20that%20shows%20how%20this%20can%20happen%20and%2C%20more%20generally%2C%20discusses%20the%20case%20of%20infinite%20decision%20points%2C%20with%20one%20player%20making%20an%20infinite%20number%20of%20decisions%20or%20a%20countably%20infinite%20set%20of%20players%2C%20each%20making%20one%20or%20a%20finite%20number%20of%20decisions%20(%3Cspan%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20data-open%3D%5C%22ref33%5C%22%20data-google-interstitial%3D%5C%22false%5C%22%3EVoorneveld%2C%202010%3C%2Fa%3E%3B%20%3Cspan%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20data-open%3D%5C%22ref14%5C%22%20data-google-interstitial%3D%5C%22false%5C%22%3ECingiz%20et%20al.%2C%202016%3C%2Fa%3E%3B%20%3Cspan%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20data-open%3D%5C%22ref31%5C%22%20data-google-interstitial%3D%5C%22false%5C%22%3ERachmilevitch%2C%202020%3C%2Fa%3E).%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cspan%20data-fn-id%3D%5C%22fn6%5C%22%3E6.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fspan%3EThereby%20raising%20troubling%20questions%20about%20the%20very%20meaning%20of%20%E2%80%98the%20game%20of%20life%E2%80%99%20(%3Cspan%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20data-open%3D%5C%22ref7%5C%22%20data-google-interstitial%3D%5C%22false%5C%22%3EBasu%2C%202022a%3C%2Fa%3E).%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cspan%20data-fn-id%3D%5C%22fn7%5C%22%3E7.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fspan%3EThe%20idea%20of%20an%20equilibrium%20of%20omitted%20strategies%20(instead%20of%20a%20vector%20of%20selected%20strategies%20as%20in%20conventional%20game%20theory)%20leads%20to%20various%20concepts%20of%20set-valued%20equilibria%20in%20games%20(see%20%3Cspan%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20data-open%3D%5C%22ref9%5C%22%20data-google-interstitial%3D%5C%22false%5C%22%3EBasu%20and%20Weibull%2C%201991%3C%2Fa%3E%3B%20%3Cspan%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20data-open%3D%5C%22ref4%5C%22%20data-google-interstitial%3D%5C%22false%5C%22%3EArad%20and%20Rubinstein%2C%202019%3C%2Fa%3E).%20These%20set-valued%20notions%20are%20germane%20to%20understanding%20the%20meaning%20of%20a%20constitution%20in%20a%20formal%20way.%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cspan%20data-fn-id%3D%5C%22fn8%5C%22%3E8.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fspan%3EAll%20real-life%20solutions%20come%20with%20caveats.%20It%20must%20be%20recognized%20that%20term%20limits%20have%20some%20disadvantages.%20It%20makes%20politicians%20focus%20on%20the%20short%20duration%20at%20the%20expense%20of%20long-term%20gains%20for%20society.%20On%20the%20other%20side%2C%20having%20term%20limits%20can%20encourage%20dynasties%2C%20which%20act%20as%20a%20substitute%20for%20one%20leader%20carrying%20on%20for%20too%20long.%20The%20reign%20of%20Kim%20Il-sung%2C%20Kim%20Jong-il%20and%20Kim%20Jong-un%2C%20from%201953%20to%20now%2C%20is%2C%20for%20all%20practical%20purpose%2C%20rule%20by%20one%20person.%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3EIt%20is%20worth%20emphasizing%20here%20that%20%E2%80%98interest%E2%80%99%20has%20come%20to%20acquire%20a%20rather%20unidimensional%20notion%20of%20%3Cem%3Eeconomic%3C%2Fem%3E%20interest%20and%20this%20has%20had%20wide%20influence%20in%20the%20way%20we%20do%20our%20analysis%20and%20formulate%20policy.%20In%20contexts%20such%20as%20the%20one%20analyzed%20in%20this%20paper%2C%20we%20have%20to%20remind%20ourselves%20that%20%E2%80%98interest%E2%80%99%20is%20a%20complicated%20multi-dimensional%20idea%20(%3Cspan%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20data-open%3D%5C%22ref32%5C%22%20data-google-interstitial%3D%5C%22false%5C%22%3ESwedberg%2C%202005%3C%2Fa%3E).%20This%20may%20make%20policymaking%20harder%2C%20but%20it%20can%20make%20policymaking%20more%20effective.%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20paper%20was%20originally%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Facademic.oup.com%2Fooec%2Farticle%2Fdoi%2F10.1093%2Fooec%2Fodad002%2F7036634%5C%22%3Epublished%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%3C%2Fem%3E%20Oxford%20Open%20Economics.%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1710855011000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F19165922%2Fimage-1989.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fhow-strong-leaders-morph-into-tyrants-assessing-the-cost-of-exit-and-heightened-ruthlessness%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Dictators%2C%20even%20those%20who%20seize%20power%20with%20the%20intention%20of%20helping%20the%20nation%2C%20frequently%20morph%20over%20time%20into%20tyrants.%20There%20may%20be%20many%20reasons%20for%20this.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fhow-strong-leaders-morph-into-tyrants-assessing-the-cost-of-exit-and-heightened-ruthlessness%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22%26quot%3BPlanet%20On%20The%20Brink%26quot%3B%3A%20UN%20As%202014-2023%20Recorded%20Hottest%20Decade%20Ever%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EGlobal%20heat%20records%20were%20%26quot%3Bsmashed%26quot%3B%20last%20year%2C%20the%20UN%20confirmed%20Tuesday%2C%20with%202023%20rounding%20out%20the%20hottest%20decade%20on%20record%2C%20as%20heatwaves%20stalked%20oceans%20and%20glaciers%20suffered%20record%20ice%20loss.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20United%20Nations'%20World%20Meteorological%20Organization%20issued%20its%20annual%20State%20of%20the%20Climate%20report%2C%20confirming%20preliminary%20data%20indicating%20that%202023%20was%20by%20far%20the%20hottest%20year%20ever%20recorded.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnd%20it%20came%20at%20the%20end%20of%20%26quot%3Bthe%20warmest%2010-year%20period%20on%20record%26quot%3B%2C%20the%20WMO%20report%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUN%20chief%20Antonio%20Guterres%20said%20the%20report%20showed%20%26quot%3Ba%20planet%20on%20the%20brink%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BEarth's%20issuing%20a%20distress%20call%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%2C%20pointing%20out%20that%20%26quot%3Bfossil%20fuel%20pollution%20is%20sending%20climate%20chaos%20off%20the%20charts%26quot%3B%2C%20and%20warning%20that%20%26quot%3Bchanges%20are%20speeding%20up%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20WMO%20said%20the%20average%20near-surface%20temperature%20was%201.45%20degrees%20Celsius%20above%20pre-industrial%20levels%20last%20year%20--%20dangerously%20close%20to%20the%20critical%201.5-degree%20threshold%20that%20countries%20agreed%20to%20avoid%20passing%20in%20the%202015%20Paris%20climate%20accords.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BNever%20have%20we%20been%20so%20close...%20to%20the%201.5C%20lower%20limit%20of%20the%20Paris%20Agreement%2C%26quot%3B%20WMO%20chief%20Andrea%20Celeste%20Saulo%20warned%20in%20a%20statement.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E-%20'Red%20alert'%20-%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20report%2C%20she%20said%2C%20should%20be%20seen%20as%20a%20%26quot%3Bred%20alert%20to%20the%20world%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGoing%20through%20the%20data%2C%20the%20organisation%20found%20that%20%26quot%3Brecords%20were%20once%20again%20broken%2C%20and%20in%20some%20cases%20smashed%26quot%3B%2C%20warning%20that%20the%20numbers%20%26quot%3Bgave%20ominous%20new%20significance%20to%20the%20phrase%20'off%20the%20charts'.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESaulo%20stressed%20that%20climate%20change%20was%20about%20much%20more%20than%20temperatures.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhat%20we%20witnessed%20in%202023%2C%20especially%20with%20the%20unprecedented%20ocean%20warmth%2C%20glacier%20retreat%20and%20Antarctic%20sea%20ice%20loss%2C%20is%20cause%20for%20particular%20concern.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOne%20especially%20worrying%20finding%20was%20that%20marine%20heatwaves%20gripped%20nearly%20a%20third%20of%20the%20global%20ocean%20on%20an%20average%20day%20last%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnd%20by%20the%20end%20of%202023%2C%20more%20than%2090%20percent%20of%20the%20ocean%20had%20experienced%20heatwave%20conditions%20at%20some%20point%20during%20the%20year%2C%20the%20WMO%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMore%20frequent%20and%20intense%20marine%20heatwaves%20will%20have%20%26quot%3Bprofound%20negative%20repercussions%20for%20marine%20ecosystems%20and%20coral%20reefs%26quot%3B%2C%20it%20warned.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20same%20time%2C%20it%20warned%20that%20key%20glaciers%20worldwide%20suffered%20the%20largest%20loss%20of%20ice%20ever%20since%20records%20began%20in%201950%2C%20%26quot%3Bdriven%20by%20extreme%20melt%20in%20both%20western%20North%20America%20and%20Europe%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20Switzerland%2C%20where%20the%20WMO%20is%20headquartered%2C%20Alpine%20glaciers%20had%20for%20instance%20lost%2010%20percent%20of%20their%20remaining%20volume%20in%20the%20past%20two%20years%20alone%2C%20it%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Antarctic%20sea%20ice%20extent%20was%20also%20%26quot%3Bby%20far%20the%20lowest%20on%20record%26quot%3B%2C%20WMO%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E-%20Rising%20sea%20levels%20-%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20fact%2C%20it%20pointed%20out%2C%20its%20maximum%20extent%20at%20the%20end%20of%20the%20southern%20winter%20was%20around%20one%20million%20square%20kilometres%20below%20the%20previous%20record%20year%20--%20equivalent%20to%20the%20size%20of%20France%20and%20Germany%20combined.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20continued%20ocean%20warming%20combined%20with%20the%20rapidly%20melting%20glaciers%20and%20ice%20sheets%20also%20drove%20the%20sea%20level%20last%20year%20to%20its%20highest%20point%20since%20satellite%20records%20began%20in%201993%2C%20WMO%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20agency%20stressed%20that%20the%20global%20mean%20sea%20level%20rise%20over%20the%20past%20decade%20(2014-2023)%20was%20more%20than%20double%20the%20rate%20in%20the%20first%20decade%20of%20satellite%20records.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20highlighted%20that%20the%20dramatic%20climate%20shifts%20are%20taking%20a%20heavy%20toll%20on%20people%20worldwide%2C%20fuelling%20extreme%20weather%20events%2C%20flooding%20and%20drought%2C%20which%20trigger%20displacement%20and%20drive%20up%20biodiversity%20loss%20and%20food%20insecurity.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20climate%20crisis%20is%20THE%20defining%20challenge%20that%20humanity%20faces%20and%20is%20closely%20intertwined%20with%20the%20inequality%20crisis%2C%26quot%3B%20Saulo%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E-%20'Glimmer%20of%20hope'%20-%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20number%20of%20people%20who%20are%20considered%20acutely%20food%20insecure%20around%20the%20world%20has%20more%20than%20doubled%2C%20from%20149%20million%20people%20prior%20to%20the%20Covid-19%20pandemic%20to%20333%20million%20at%20the%20end%20of%202023%2C%20WMO%20pointed%20out.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20UN's%20weather%20and%20climate%20agency%20did%20however%20highlight%20one%20%26quot%3Bglimmer%20of%20hope%26quot%3B%3A%20surging%20renewable%20energy%20generation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELast%20year%2C%20renewable%20energy%20generation%20capacity%20--%20mainly%20from%20solar%2C%20wind%20and%20hydropower%20--%20increased%20by%20nearly%2050%20percent%20from%202022%2C%20it%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGuterres%20also%20emphasised%20that%20there%20was%20an%20upside%20to%20the%20findings.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20world%2C%20he%20insisted%2C%20still%20has%20a%20chance%20to%20keep%20the%20planet's%20long-term%20temperature%20rise%20below%20the%201.5C%20threshold%20and%20%26quot%3Bavoid%20the%20worst%20of%20climate%20chaos%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20know%20how%20to%20do%20it.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E(Except%20for%20the%20headline%2C%20this%20story%20has%20not%20been%20edited%20by%20ND