%5C%22%3EIn%20the%2035%20months%20between%20their%20first%20receipt%20of%20funding%20through%20electoral%20bonds%20in%20July%202018%20and%20the%20Bengal%20assembly%20election%20in%20April-May%202021%2C%20the%20party%20earned%20Rs%20285.14%20crore%20through%20electoral%20bonds.%20The%20funding%20pattern%20saw%20a%20massive%20change%20after%20her%20return%20to%20power%20for%20a%20third%20straight%20term%20in%20May%202021.%20The%20party%20earned%20Rs%201%2C420.05%20crore%20in%20the%2031%20months%20between%20July%202021%20and%20January%202024%20%E2%80%93%20a%20five-fold%20increase%20in%20monthly%20average.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EEven%20during%20the%20pre-2021%20assembly%20election%20period%2C%20the%20fluctuation%20in%20getting%20funding%20is%20discernable.%20As%20per%20electoral%20bond%20encashment%20data%20and%20the%20party%E2%80%99s%20submissions%20before%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20that%20have%20been%20published%20by%20the%20Election%20Commission%20of%20India%20(ECI)%20under%20the%20apex%20court%E2%80%99s%20instructions%2C%20the%20party%20ruling%20Bengal%20since%202011%20earned%20Rs%20150.5%20crore%20through%20electoral%20bonds%20in%2011%20months%20from%20July%202018%20to%20May%202019.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EBy%20the%20time%20of%20Lok%20Sabha%20election%202019%2C%20the%20BJP%20was%20far%20ahead%20of%20everyone%20else%20%E2%80%93%20earning%20Rs.%203964.89%20crore%20through%20electoral%20bonds%20by%20May%202019.%20It%20got%20Rs%20210%20crore%20in%20January-February-March%202018%20when%20no%20other%20party%20had%20anything%20in%20their%20account.%20By%20March%202019%2C%20it%20had%20earned%20another%20Rs%201%2C450.89%20crore%20and%20another%20whopping%20Rs%202%2C304%20crore%20came%20in%20April-May%202019.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Ftop-five-political-parties-saw-electoral-bonds-fortunes-turning-with-election-wins-and-losses%5C%22%3E