0Photo%3A%20Unsplash%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EFunding%20pattern%20during%20the%202019%20Lok%20Sabha%20election%20in%20West%20Bengal%20reveals%20that%20over%20Rs%20500%20crore%20was%20pumped%20into%20the%20political%20funding%20from%20West%20Bengal-based%20business%20groups%20like%20Mahendra%20Jalan%E2%80%99s%20MKJ%20group%20and%20Sanjiv%20Goenka%E2%80%99s%20RP%20Sanjiv%20Goenka%20group%2C%20among%20others.%20It%20maybe%20noted%20that%20in%20September%202022%2C%20the%20Central%20Bureau%20of%20Investigation%20(CBI)%20started%20an%20investigation%20against%20the%20RP%20Sanjiv%20Goenka%20group%20of%20companies%20on%20thce%20harge%20of%20involvement%20in%20the%20allocations%20of%20coal%20blocks%20in%20the%20past.%20October%202022%20saw%20spending%20of%20Rs%2040%20crore%20%E2%80%93%20Rs%2015%20crore%20from%20Crescent%20Power%2C%20and%20Rs%2025%20crore%20from%20Dhariwal%20Infrastructure.%20Two%20Sanjiv%20Goenka-led%20firms%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.deccanherald.com%2Findia%2Ftwo-rp-sanjiv-goenka-firms-flagged-by-cag-for-rigging-coal-auction-among-top-20-electoral-bond-donors-report-2939523%5C%22%20data-stringify-link%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.deccanherald.com%2Findia%2Ftwo-rp-sanjiv-goenka-firms-flagged-by-cag-for-rigging-coal-auction-among-top-20-electoral-bond-donors-report-2939523%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%20data-sk%3D%5C%22tooltip_parent%5C%22%3Ewere%20flagged%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0by%20the%20Comptroller%20and%20Auditor%20General%2C%20the%20country%E2%80%99s%20top%20auditor%2C%20for%20rigging%20coal%20auctions.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EThe%20TMC%20did%20not%20have%20much%20fortune%20in%20tapping%20those%20fundings%2C%20as%20their%20earning%20through%20electoral%20bonds%20during%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20election%20months%20of%20April-May%20stood%20at%20Rs%2053.22%20crore.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EAfter%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20election%20setback%2C%20in%20which%20the%20TMC%E2%80%99s%20Lok%20Sabha%20tally%20came%20down%20from%2034%20in%202014%20to%2022%20in%202019%20%E2%80%93%20funding%20shrunk.%20They%20got%20another%20Rs%20134.64%20crore%20in%20two%20years%20till%20May%202021%2C%20the%20end%20of%20the%20Bengal%20assembly%20election.%20During%20the%20assembly%20election%20months%20of%20April-May%202021%2C%20their%20earning%20from%20electoral%20bonds%20stood%20at%20Rs%2045.4%20crore.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EBut%20everything%20changed%20after%20Banerjee%E2%80%99s%20TMC%20defeated%20the%20BJP%E2%80%99s%20high-voltage%20campaign%20and%20returned%20to%20power%20with%20a%20massive%20mandate%2C%20indicating%20a%20stable%20government%20for%20the%20next%20five%20years.%20They%20got%20%E2%80%98rewarded%E2%80%99%20in%20the%20very%20first%20trance%20of%20electoral%20bond%20sales%20in%20July%202021.%20It%20became%20a%20100-crore-month%20for%20the%20party%20%E2%80%93%20earning%20Rs%20107.4%20crore.%20Of%20this%2C%20Rs%2061%20crore%20came%20on%20a%20single%20day%20on%20July%2012.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EHere%E2%80%99s%20the%20party%E2%80%99s%20rather%20startling%20earnings%20on%20some%20days%20in%20January%202022%20%E2%80%93%20Rs%2069%20crore%20on%20January%2010%2C%20Rs%2029%20crore%20on%20January%2011%2C%20Rs%2060%20crore%20on%20January%2013%2C%20and%20Rs%2051%20crore%20on%20January%2014.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EOverall%2C%20they%20earned%20Rs%20482.6%20crore%20in%2010%20months%20between%20July%202021%20and%20March%202022%2C%20and%20Rs.%20325%20crore%20between%20April%202022%20and%20March%202023.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EThese%20big%20fundings%20came%20at%20a%20time%20when%20the%20TMC%20was%20aiming%20big%20to%20expand%20beyond%20Bengal%20and%20carried%20out%20high-voltage%20campaigns%20in%20Goa%2C%20Tripura%20and%20Meghalaya.%20Their%20expansion%20bids%2C%20though%2C%20failed%20rather%20miserably%2C%20except%20for%20Meghalaya%20to%20some%20extent.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EDespite%20these%20failures%20outside%20West%20Bengal%2C%C2%A0funding%20flow%20increased%C2%A0as%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20election%20inched%20closer.%20They%20got%20Rs%20171.27%20crore%20through%20electoral%20bonds%20in%20October%202023%20and%20Rs%20130%20crore%20in%20January%202024.%20Of%20them%2C%20Rs%2098%20crore%20came%20on%20a%20single%20day%20%E2%80%93%20January%2010.%20Overall%2C%20the%20party%20got%20Rs%C2%A0%20612%20crore%20between%20April%202023%20and%20January%202024.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EThis%20massive%20funds%20inflow%20has%20taken%20the%20party%20way%20ahead%20of%20other%20regional%20parties%2C%20ranking%20third%20among%20the%20beneficiaries%20of%20the%20electoral%20bonds%20scheme%2C%20with%20a%20cumulative%20income%20of%20Rs%201%2C705%20crore%2C%20which%20is%20roughly%2010%25%20of%20total%20electoral%20bond%20encashments%20of%20Rs%2016%2C518%20crore%20by%20all%20parties.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EThey%20stood%20only%20behind%20the%20BJP%20(8%2C251.8%20crore%20OR%2050%25)%20and%20the%20Congress%20(Rs.%201%2C952%20crore%20or%2011.82%25).%C2%A0However%2C%20their%20income%20since%20their%20return%20to%20power%20in%20May%202021%20is%20higher%20than%20the%20Congress%20during%20the%20same%20period%2C%20despite%20the%20latter%E2%80%99s%20nationwide%20presence.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20a%20result%20of%20such%20fund%20inflow%2C%20the%20TMC%E2%80%99s%20assets%20rose%20quicker%20than%20others.%20The%20Association%20for%20Democratic%20Reforms%20(ADR)%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmailtrack.io%2Fl%2Fbce6a5b4baa0254ce4f1344fa79ee8e365e192bc%3Furl%3Dhttps%253A%252F%252Fadrindia.org%252Fcontent%252Frs-6000-crore-bjp-has-highest-assets-among-top-eight-political-parties-adr-report%26u%3D7302199%26signature%3D83ae53585a54c1e2%5C%22%20data-saferedirecturl%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.google.com%2Furl%3Fq%3Dhttps%3A%2F%2Fmailtrack.io%2Fl%2Fbce6a5b4baa0254ce4f1344fa79ee8e365e192bc%3Furl%253Dhttps%25253A%25252F%25252Fadrindia.org%25252Fcontent%25252Frs-6000-crore-bjp-has-highest-assets-among-top-eight-political-parties-adr-report%2526u%253D7302199%2526signature%253D83ae53585a54c1e2%26amp%3Bsource%3Dgmail%26amp%3Bust%3D1710917122332000%26amp%3Busg%3DAOvVaw3JwsgvwLZO7qGjCE5F7SuQ%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3E%3C%2Fspan%3Epointed%20out%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0in%202023%20that%20the%20TMC%E2%80%99s%20total%20assets%20increased%20from%20Rs.%20182%20crore%20in%202020-21%20to%20Rs.%20458%20crore%20in%202021-22.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20huge%20earning%20by%20Mamata%20Banerjee%E2%80%99s%20party%20has%20raised%20many%20eyebrows%2C%20considering%20that%20West%20Bengal%20is%20not%20among%20India%E2%80%99s%20top%20economies%20and%20that%20the%20state%20has%20not%20seen%20any%20big-ticket%20industrial%20projects%20during%20Banerjee%E2%80%99s%2012-year%20rule.%20The%20government%2C%20however%2C%20has%20been%20looking%20for%20potential%20bidders%20for%20two%20deep-sea%20port%20projects%20in%20East%20Midnapore%20district%E2%80%99s%20Tajpur%20and%20South%2024-Parganas%20district%E2%80%99s%20Kulpi%20and%20a%20major%20coal%20mining%20project%20in%20Birbhum%20district%20and%20is%20spending%20a%20lot%20on%20roadways%20infrastructure.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EWest%20Bengal%20is%20India%E2%80%99s%20fourth-most%20populous%20state%2C%20after%20Uttar%20Pradesh%2C%20Maharashtra%20and%20Bihar%2C%20and%20has%20the%20third%20highest%20number%20of%20Lok%20Sabha%20seats%20%E2%80%93%2042%2C%20after%20Uttar%20Pradesh%20(80)%20and%20Maharashtra%20(44).%20It%20is%20India%E2%80%99s%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fslbcbengal.pnbindia.in%2FStateEconomy.asp%5C%22%20data-saferedirecturl%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.google.com%2Furl%3Fq%3Dhttps%3A%2F%2Fslbcbengal.pnbindia.in%2FStateEconomy.asp%26amp%3Bsource%3Dgmail%26amp%3Bust%3D1710917122332000%26amp%3Busg%3DAOvVaw14gGfgczs1_x9neABoblpm%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esixth-largest%20economy%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EThe%20publication%20of%20the%20electoral%20bond%20details%20has%20so%20far%20caused%20the%20BJP%20a%20great%20deal%20of%20embarrassment%2C%20as%20it%20is%20being%20pointed%20out%20how%20companies%20that%20faced%20probes%20by%20central%20investigating%20agencies%20like%20the%20Central%20Bureau%20of%20Investigation%20(CBI)%20and%20the%20Enforcement%20Directorate%20(ED)%20gave%20generously%20founded%20political%20parties%20soon%20after%20raid%20by%20such%20agencies%2C%20prompting%20many%20to%20suspect%20institutional%20extortion.%20The%20TMC%20has%20maintained%20a%20complete%20silence%20during%20this%20entire%20episode.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EThe%20only%20comment%20has%20come%20from%20the%20party%E2%80%99s%20Delhi-based%20Rajya%20Sabha%20MP%2C%20Saket%20Gokhale%2C%20who%20described%20the%20apex%20court%20verdict%20calling%20the%20scheme%20unconstitutional%20as%20%E2%80%9Ca%20historic%20one.%E2%80%9D%20But%C2%A0over%20the%20next%20four%20weeks%2C%C2%A0no%20word%20came%20from%20the%20party%E2%80%99s%20top%20leaders%20%E2%80%94%20chairperson%20Mamata%20Banerjee%2C%20or%20the%20all-India%20general%20secretary%2C%20her%20nephew%20Abhishek%20Banerjee.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EEven%20as%20the%20central%20government%20institution%2C%20the%20State%20Bank%20of%20India%20(SBI)%2C%20has%20appeared%20to%20try%20its%20best%20to%20convince%20the%20court%20not%20to%20make%20public%20the%20secret%20serial%20numbers%20that%20can%20connect%20donors%20with%20recipients%2C%20and%20has%20so%20far%20failed%2C%20the%20TMC%20shows%20no%20sign%20of%20celebration.%C2%A0It%20is%20not%20often%20that%20they%20miss%20an%20opportunity%20to%20target%20the%20BJP.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20party%E2%80%99s%20comments%2C%20if%20any%2C%20will%20come%20only%20after%20seeing%20what%20transpires%20in%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20finally.%20Let%20us%20first%20see%20if%20all%20serial%20numbers%20are%20made%20public%20and%20what%20the%20people%20can%20make%20out%20of%20them%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20a%20state%20minister%2C%20who%20did%20not%20want%20to%20be%20identified.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EThe%20minister%20argued%20that%20it%20was%20not%20necessary%20that%20there%20must%20be%20a%20%E2%80%9Cquid%20pro%20quo%E2%80%9D%20behind%20the%20TMC%E2%80%99s%20inflow%20of%20funds.%20%E2%80%9CMany%20industrialists%20are%20fed%20up%20with%20the%20BJP%E2%80%99s%20rule%20and%20want%20to%20end%20it.%20Mamata%20Banerjee%20being%20one%20of%20the%20leading%20opposition%20faces%2C%20it%20is%20highly%20possible%20that%20some%20of%20these%20people%20would%20like%20to%20back%20her%20to%20end%20the%20BJP%E2%80%99s%20tyranny.%20People%20who%20want%20us%20to%20fight%20for%20an%20inclusive%20India%20may%20also%20have%20supported%20us%20with%20funding.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EIn%20any%20case%2C%20even%20if%20the%20serial%20numbers%20are%20released%20and%20people%20get%20to%20know%20who%20funded%20the%20TMC%2C%20the%20party%20is%20ready%20with%20its%20line%20of%20defence.%20They%20would%20repeat%20what%20they%20wrote%20in%20the%20affidavit%20submitted%20before%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20in%20the%20electoral%20bond%20case.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EThe%20party%20wrote%2C%20%E2%80%9CThe%20Bonds%20are%20bearer%20bonds%20and%20no%20details%20of%20the%20purchasers%20are%20printed%20on%20the%20bond.%20Further%2C%20most%20of%20the%20bonds%20were%20sent%20to%20our%20office%20and%20dropped%20in%20the%20drop%20box%20or%20sent%20through%20messengers%20from%20various%20persons%20who%20wished%20to%20support%20our%20party.%20Thus%2C%20we%20do%20not%20have%20names%20and%20other%20details%20of%20the%20buyers%20of%20the%20Bonds.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EIn%20short%2C%20even%20as%20parties%20like%20Tamil%20Nadu%E2%80%99s%20Dravida%20Munnetra%20Kazhagam%20and%20Karnataka%E2%80%99s%20Janata%20Dal%20(Secular)%20had%20voluntarily%20disclosed%20donor%20details%20at%20the%20supreme%20court%E2%80%99s%20call%20for%20transparency%2C%20the%20TMC%E2%80%99s%20answer%20is%20short%20and%20simple%3A%20%E2%80%9CWe%20do%20not%20know%20who%20funded%20us.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1710853156000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2018%2F05%2F17133238%2FScreen-Shot-2018-05-17-at-1.32.17-PM.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fhow-the-2021-bengal-assembly-election-victory-changed-tmcs-financial-fortune%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Of%20the%20party%E2%80%99s%20total%20Rs.%201%2C705%20crore%20earnings%20through%20electoral%20bonds%2C%20Rs%201%2C420%20crore%20or%2083%25%20came%20after%20returning%20to%20power%20for%20a%20third%20term%20in%20May%202021.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A29%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fhow-the-2021-bengal-assembly-election-victory-changed-tmcs-financial-fortune%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22'Red%20alert%20to%20the%20world'%20after%202023%20plagued%20with%20climate%20'misery%20and%20mayhem'%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1710853140000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fe3.365dm.com%2F23%2F10%2F768x432%2Fskynews-argentina-wildfires_6317523.png%3F20231011080738%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Fclimate-report-issues-red-alert-warning-after-record-breaking-temperatures-caused-misery-and-mayhem-in-2023-13098034%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Extreme%20weather%20events%20were%20%26quot%3Boff%20the%20charts%26quot%3B%20in%202023%2C%20according%20to%20a%20new%20report%20aiming%20to%20send%20a%20%26quot%3Bred%20alert%26quot%3B%20to%20the%20world%20about%20the%20need%20for%20action%20on%20climate%20change.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A34%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%